name: J Wang
snippet: Ordered take away lunch and received this burned toastie (hidden downside) which is not eatable. I didn‚Äôt even think to check the food inside the take away box when left as I always trust the food qualify from PCP. Had to rush back to the cafe and asked for a refund and I ended up with no lunch-break time/food for this work day.

name: Manish Rai
snippet: TLDR/Long story short: Wrong pricing online, overpriced, ridiculously small portions, busy and long wait times. Support a small cafe instead. Imagine coming to a cafe with an online menu that says Avo on Toast is 14.50. You come in and it‚Äôs now 18.50 with weekend surcharge of 10%. You‚Äôre paying 20 dollars for Avocado on Toast which is stupid. The coffee was priced well, OR SO WE THOUGHT Portions come in. Most cafes have 2 slices of sourdough or a large sourdough toast. This is the TINIEST toast I have seen. Employees excuse is that you‚Äôre paying for the ingredients on top of it. The normal plain toast which we got is also TINY. Lastly, look at the coffee compared to an IPhone XS. This is so tiny. I would get a full cup elsewhere for 4.50. Employees excuse is the cup size is on the counter, which in my opinion is not readily seen. Paid $60 as students who didn‚Äôt realise they had increased the price this much compared to their online menu and had weekend surcharge. Also they are so busy. Genuinely don‚Äôt know why people are supporting them with these small portions and high prices

name: Lisa
snippet: Drinks order was taken and drinks never arrived, had to chase it up. Had to get up to find someone and ask them to take our food order. Ordered chicken and waffles and chicken burger which were both delicious until I discovered a very long dark hair in my burger. They did take it off the bill (obviously) but my wife was too grossed out to finish her food and we promptly left. Would not return.

name: Angel Manuel
snippet: I came here twice, poor service. I ordered green tea, I received black tea. I was okay with the first mix-up, but I ordered breakfast avo on toast it never came...I was there for a good hour, luckily I was working and sipped on my tea to distract me with the time but I had to cancel. When I advised the girl at the cash register all she said was sorry, here is your bill. I even asked if the kitchen received my order ? she said "yes, sorry about that' no explanation and her sorry was as empty as my stomach. I even thought I would again order coffees to go just to support local business but having some to reflect, I didn't feel valued and I don't think I will come back.

name: Jisoo
snippet: We came here because the coffee shop we were gonna go to was closed. We ordered housemade granola and miso ramen, and we were able to receive the food after 35 minutes. There weren‚Äôt many ppl. We definitely ordered ramen, but they gave us bibimbap. But fortunately, they switched to ramen. Granola had too little yogurt. But the servers were all nice.

name: Jayson Heron
snippet: Came for breakfast on a Saturday. Started out well & food was good, but then it got busy & staff ignored us taking 1/2 hour just to order a second coffee. We also had to ask for the table to be cleared several times. All this is forgivable given current staff shortages, but the attitude was not. Very rude ‚Äògood on you‚Äô comments & other behaviour from the supervisor as if we were doing them a favour by being there.

name: Sammi Ngo
snippet: The venue is cool, but the staff is rude and arrogant - especially the staff serving takeaway orders at the bar. Not a great experience, and you don‚Äôt feel welcome as customers there. Food is okay and coffee is average.

name: David Walton
snippet: Yesterday I ordered a takeaway LFW & a cream bun. I thought the girl said $9‚Äôs something and paid. Later when I checked my card App I realised I had been charged $19.76! Never again.

name: Wardrobe Stealer
snippet: Overrated.. Servings are small, pricing is high for what it is, staff are rude, we had to keep moving at the shared table to make room for people arriving, food is average, weekend surcharges.. list goes on Lots of better cafes in area

name: bella donovan
snippet: So overpriced. Spent $13 and got 1 piece of toast. I know its meant to be a trendy place but geez. I got takeaway and didnt realise until I had already left, otherwise I would have complained. I was honestly shocked when I opened the box and saw one tiny piece of toast. Disappointing, because adding another piece with a bit more avo, would make all the difference. Wont be going back.. sick of getting ripped off.

name: James Dalgety
snippet: Apart from the Banana bread, it was terrible. Maybe it was today's chef but my partners fritters were so mushy and undercooked they were not edible. Sent them back. Ordered an extra egg with my meal, egg white was very undercooked/snotty. I asked for them to cook the egg white through for me after it came out. And it came back again still snottyüòÖ. Won't be back. Don't recommend it.

name: Ahmed Jadid
snippet: I wanted an outdoor table to sit down for breakfast and was askes to sit at the bar by one of the male workers. When requested if i would like to start with coffee i asked for a mocha in a takeaway cup. I then saw a female worker direct a couple to the outdoor table i actually wanted. Several minutes later the same bloke brought me a coffee in a mug... Fed up i requested my "takeaway" coffee and stated that i won't be eating breakfast here because i was sat down at the bar whilst newcomers were straight away sat down before me. Not the slightest care or concern on his face and had the nerve to charge $6.60 for a coffee the size of plum. You try to be nice towards people and hopw they treat you well but alas

name: Reza Bagheri
snippet: Not happy. Beans swimmimg in water with 2 spinach leaves and an egg accompanied by 2 smallest pieces of toast you have ever seen in your life sets you back $26!!!!!! Never again.

name: K
snippet: $6 for a coffee and an unnecessary card surcharge on top. Service is poor and seems disorganised , isn‚Äôt worth the hipster mark-up anymore

name: Julie Parker
snippet: First negative review I‚Äôve written - I only had 1 slice of the generic banana bread and an oat late and was charged $15.50 very overpriced!

name: SF P
snippet: I just got in town and was looking for a nice place to send some work emails while enjoying the local surroundings. This was not the place to do so unfortunately as it does not have Wifi (!) and the policy here seems to favour a quick turnaround at the tables rather than fostering a relaxing environment. The coffee I ordered came with a card slip explaining all about it, but nevertheless it did not taste very good: it was watery and bland. Nevertheless there was a nice crowd of people, so I guess that if you are in a group, intend to have as much food as possible and stay a very short period of time, this might indeed be a good place.

name: priyesh patel
snippet: For a cafe that seems to pride themselves on coffee, what was put forward as a takeaway coffee is something would struggle to compete with instant coffee. The milk was scorching hot as if the barista has lost all sensation in his hand and unable to feel what 65 degrees is.

name: Rob Gore
snippet: Avo was off, bacon and bread were stale and coffee was really weak. Hardly ate anything and charged $70

name: J B
snippet: Disappointing that basics like toast and eggs are not done properly. No condiments given. Just a miserable egg sitting on toast.

name: Stephanie Cheng
snippet: I will never go to this place again. Part from the guy who got us a table, the place was a complete mess. Service was sarcastic, food was mediocre yet overpriced and to too it all off, there was a stone in my salmon salad. When I told the waitress, they passed it around and said the chef would take a look at it. No apologies, no acknowledgement of the health hazard. What a total joke. So many cool joints in Surry, there is no need to pay for such a bad brunch experience. Kudos to the guy with the cool haircut that gave us our seats - you were lovely.

name: RODERICK GAWTHROP
snippet: Have been to this place a few times now since moving to Surry hills and the only consistent thing about this place is the service. Each time I was made to wait whilst they continued to have a casual chat with a customer that had already ordered, and was never acknowledged. After waiting a few minutes after the chat had seemingly ended, still no acknowledgment so I just had to awkwardly blurt out my order. Very slow service, and no acknowledgment when giving you the coffee, even after saying ‚Äúthanks‚Äù. I‚Äôm not asking for a lengthy chat but a simple ‚Äúhi‚Äù would be nice. But not once, any of the times I‚Äôve been there. The only saving grace is the coffee is reasonable, but not on par with the seeming arrogance that the staff (and I think owner) treat the space and other customers. Avoid this place, there is better service and better coffee just 10 steps across the road.

name: Emily S
snippet: I like the coffee, just wish they used a different oat milk than Minor Figures. Would love to go back there if they did

name: Tyler C
snippet: This is quite annoying to write as the bagels and coffee are fantastic BUT the service is appalling. The guys who work here just have mates that sit there chatting to them all day, have zero care in the world when serving and are just keen to finish their 4 hour stint within the hole in the wall. I know you are probably succeeding with revenue but you suck.

name: Andrew Vild
snippet: Super pretentious. Were really rude to us when we asked about a coffee loyalty card, the response was rudely "coffee is loyalty enough". Their coffee is actually terrible. Oh and more expensive than anywhere else around. Go to Bread And Brew or Sample instead!

name: Ramli AA
snippet: No good test coffee just test of milk.i ask extra hot he do it cold he smiles for female but male no

name: Elvira Sojli
snippet: Nothing like the hype it generates. Standard coffee, a bit bitter and burned.

name: Jox Lox
snippet: Disappointing coffee. No flavor. Expensive. Small smaller than average.

name: Damien Oliver
snippet: Overpriced and tiny!

name: Potatohands Kim
snippet: It is really similar with Artificial cafe. It is not my type. But my friends liked though.

name: Will T
snippet: Disappointing coffee experience - coffee itself was overhyped but more importantly, the service was terrible. Classic example of a local speciality coffee shop that became cocky after being featured on Broadsheet. Sad to say this is not the first time that this has happened. Hope Dan and Shoji goes back to basics before losing loyal and new customers.

name: Martin Gifford
snippet: I asked for a normal size latte. They gave me a mini-latte. It turns out their normal/regular latte size is mini. The only alternative to that is large. So you have a choice betweeen too small and too large. I've travelled all over Australia and all over Planete Earth, and I've never seen coffee sizes like that. And they don't warn you by showing the sizes. So you are waiting around for a ridiculous experience. Bad start to the day.

name: Blake Usher
snippet: Absolutely amazing coffee. First bad experience with service. Girl with short blonde hair either has poor product knowledge and covers her embarassment by being rude, or is just naturally rude.

name: Aaron Nolan
snippet: Great coffee. They clearly know what to make but no option for a mug to have in (not great environmentally) and I have to say that the air of superiority and lack of even basic manners like a greeting smile or a thank you was very off putting. I got the sense they thought I should be grateful for going or something. Won‚Äôt be going back.

name: Pei Rou Shen
snippet: Cold brew was nice. But received a latte that was made from the previous extract of espresso, not fresh espresso result of that was plain cup of coffee, couldn‚Äôt tasted the fragrance at all.

name: M K
snippet: HOMELESS COFFEE SNOBS!!! The staff at this ‚Äúestablishment‚Äù are arrogant, fake coffee experts. The truth is that, the coffee is VERY AVERAGE and the staff is broke and homeless. They also don‚Äôt know how to manage a queue, as two people blatantly cut in front of me. GOOD LUCK WITH YOUR GARBAGE COFFEE and HOMELESS BROKE STAFF.

name: Tim Chapman
snippet: Coffee tasted like water and iced chocolate was brown milk with no flavour

name: Lucy Taylor
snippet: Pretentious.

name: David P
snippet: The service and ambience was alright. But the food was very bad. Such a poor quality for such a price. The meet was undercooked, chips overcooked. In overall had a very bad experience. And the table was wobbly. Being in Surry Hills there are plenty good places to visit.

name: Claire Carrico
snippet: I have been coming here at Cuckoo Callay for a long time, I was stunned by the very indifferent service. This Man on the floor used the phone instead of paying attention to my order, I waited 20 mins for my coffee for the very first time.This man needs a training or he will ruin the good reputation of this place.

name: Kelly Crawford
snippet: Dropped in this morning at 8am for breaky & was told I couldn‚Äôt sit down as they were having internet problems ???? I asked if they could just take a manual order (I was the only one there!) & again NO . No effort whatsoever. Completely understanding of technical issues but a smile and some customer service wouldn‚Äôt go astray! Honestly‚Ä¶. I would‚Äôve been happy with a coffee while I waited. It wasn‚Äôt offered. Thank goodness for Shuk across the road - Saturday morning saved.

name: John Lawrance
snippet: Terrible. Staff ignored us and ordering system did not work. All about throughput and zero service. Do NOT go there.

name: Mayra Custodio
snippet: My husband and I went there this morning with a friend. They first asked us to wait for 15 minutes as apparently it had a lot of people but once they called us in to get a table on the second floor we noticed a lot of tables available. So they let you waiting so the place looks really busy (like, really?) After finishing our meal, we headed to pay and we asked if they could split the bill as we wanted to use our voucher from government, the lady asked us to then pay downstairs. Once with another staff member downstairs to pay she told us they do not split the bills. My husband explained we wanted to use the voucher but she kept saying "no, I don't know why upstairs they said that but we do not split bills. Only one voucher allowed". Honestly it was pathetic. At the end we needed to pay mostly with our money instead of with the vouchers. Isn't it what the vouchers are for? Never coming back to this place.

name: Steve Clark
snippet: Got the drinks but then lost our food menu no apology and no compensation not going back over rated and over priced

name: Cassie Rogers
snippet: When I told the waitress there was a hair in my food she apologised and went to get a replacement. She was really lovely but then a few minutes later the manager came over and said she couldn‚Äôt find the hair. She was extremely rude and implied that I‚Äôd made it up. The managers handling of the situation turned it into a bigger situation than it needed to be and made me and my friend feel unwelcome.

name: Alexis Rose
snippet: Service is terrible! I work in hospitality so this is really disheartening as I make sure that I‚Äôm always polite to other hospitality workers. The food was so overpriced, my partner and I got two sides each (handful of mushrooms/egg) and we were charged $40. FORTY DOLLARS. Will not be returning, which is annoying as I live in Surry Hills. Do not recommend.

name: Louise Ayling
snippet: Super disappointing vegan options for a surry hills restaurant! The menu says to ask wait staff about vegan options but the waitress had to double check and the items she told me to order had to be seriously changed to actually make them vegan. Ie ended up getting avo toast with tomatoes and edamame after removing feta, eggs and pesto. No actual vegan items on the menu! I also ordered kimchi as an extra and it was on my bill but not added to my meal. Super sad because this place has killer breakfast but its just not vegan friendly.

name: Nicholas Desai
snippet: Great location and good food, however you guys lost out on service. I approached the front counter for a serviette and was sent back by a waitress with arm tattoos. She never asked what I was after, she rudely said "we have table service, we will come to your table". I then ordered the popular Reuben Sandwich and it arrived with a HAIR on the meat. We asked for it to be replaced. While waiting on a fresh order, the same waitress with tattoos decides to explain to us that it wasnt a human hair but "a hair from the muscle" (whatever that meant). I'm quite disappointed because I couldn't enjoy the meal as much as I would have liked.

name: Hariahna De Lemos
snippet: The owner wouldn‚Äôt let us play pool

name: Alexander K.
snippet: 2 slices of bread with avocado for $20. Overpriced much?! Nothing special

name: Simone Kuhar
snippet: The food was tasty and the service was good, however the 'vegan option' for the pumpkin dish was to remove egg and feta, with no vegan protein alternative offered. I asked to add mushroom to replace the egg and feta and they agreed but then charged them as an extra $6 side. It's 2022 and I expected better.

name: Kara M
snippet: Coffee was good, service slow. Asked for an inside table when booking online but was seated outside (at the only table outside) on a cold blustery morning with two kids in tow. Food ok, not up to the standard as seen in online photos. Overall a bit hit & miss

name: B Onay
snippet: Ordered a juice and it never came, then ordered a coffee and it never came. Food was ok but overpriced for a piece of pumpkin, an egg and a smear of beetroot. Was still hungry afterwards. Noticed on the receipt when we left that the still charged for the juice and also 10% service charge.

name: David Lett
snippet: Two stars as the coffee was nice, staff were insanely understaffed on a Sunday but without a doubt trying their hardest and extremely apologetic so no complaints there. We ordered around 20-30 mins after being sat with water, got the Muesli which was served with no more a table spoon of yoghurt which was spread out scarcely so it was even hard to pick up with the spoon, had to scrape the plate to get anything not to mention it was hidden under a cup of nuts to make it look like you were given more than what was actually there, it was a disappointment considering it was $18 or $16 ? They had Two different prices advertised. Maybe we caught them on a bad day but it was definitely enough for me to not return.

name: Patrick Hart
snippet: Drove out of our way to go there. Posted hours said it was open, yet they were closed. Might be good but I wouldn‚Äôt know.

name: Robert Beecroft
snippet: Unfortunately quite disappointed with my experience. Ordered the poached eggs with ocean trout. The trout piece itself was quite dry and also small considering the price. The eggs and salad had no salt so we‚Äôre literally flavourless. I had to put chutney over half the dish to get some flavour. The 2 stars is only for the coffee which was nice. A shame as I had his place saved to visit for a while and was quite let down.

name: Darragh Foley
snippet: Scabby portions, thin "slices" of sourdough and barely 1/3 an avocado over 3 slices with a bit of salt and half a lime slice. 18.50$ ü§î nah

name: Fangyu W
snippet: Good food but poor service

name: Tisha Huynh
snippet: Food: 5/5 | Service: 5/5 | Atmosphere: 5/5More

name: Lenka Ariel
snippet: Came for brunch on Saturday! Food, service & atmosphere were absolutely outstanding ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ the Avocado toast was sensational & the Fried chicken waffles were to die for. Such a interesting mix of flavours ‚ô° Mimosa coming in wine glass was def nice surprise too! Very recommended :)Food: 5/5 | Service: 5/5 | Atmosphere: 5/5 ‚Ä¶More

name: Himiko Mori
snippet: One of fav cafe in Sydney city!Little bit packed in weekends but not long to wait :)Perfect place to catch up friends with great coffee and meals!

name: wowchun
snippet: Good quality and service but long queue

name: Nicole
snippet: average

name: Seohyeon Jeong
snippet: (Translated by Google) The coffee was good and the interior of the shop was stylish. Water bottles and glasses per table are provided even if you just order coffee. name: Julie Tolsgaard
snippet: Wonderful coffee in Surry Hills! The customer service is oustanding and the decor is beautiful ‚ú®

name: Kate T
snippet: Spent $30 on a toast with avo and bacon + coffee. The whole toast was hard (not just the crust), and nearly impossible to cut. Quite disappointing.

name: Yury Kim
snippet: Crumbed eggs on toast was yummy and fried chicken waffle was not bad. But There is a 10% surcharges on weekends.

name: Reem AlGarawi
snippet: (Translated by Google) A very special place for breakfast and coffee. We tried them: - crumbed eggs on toast - French Toast The eggs were special and tasted different. name: Amalia Halim
snippet: This place is a bit crowded, but good food and friendly serviceRecommended dishes Fried Chick Waffle ‚Ä¶More

name: Liza L
snippet: Came here for a light breakfast. The eggs on toast was surprisingly good. Great coffee, too. Service was good.

name: Robert Zheng
snippet: Worth trying. Bustling cafe/brunch establishment that has a loyal following. Solid coffee, Mocha was a little too sweet. Crumbed Eggs are a nice solid staple. Wagyu burger was okay - wasn't very tender and wasn't very beefy. Uni mushroom pasta was the standout hit, very umami, cooked perfectly, cleaned out instantly. Takes AMEX.

name: Jennie Hamlett
snippet: Great breakfast, coffee and juices. Will definitely be going back.

name: Chinee Loh
snippet: Great design, excellent coffee, and food was very delicious and aesthetically pleasing! Had the avo toast and an oat latte. Went for brunch on a Thursday afternoon, had a good time on my own ‚ò∫Ô∏è

name: Alexandra S
snippet: I think they make the best coffee in Australia! Definitely will be coming there for coffee every day again on our next trip to Sydney

name: Angela R
snippet: Only had a flat white but it was as good as it gets

name: Bin Xu
snippet: My bill was presented on the table just when my food was finished, very rude!

name: Rami Mallis
snippet: The stingiest, most pathetic b&e roll I‚Äôve ever come across. Produce prices must be hitting margins hard to be serving a role with half a rasher and a sneeze of scrambled eggs. Not good enough for $15.

name: Brad Buzzard
snippet: $6.58 for a soy latte. Nearly $20 for a stock-standard bacon and egg roll. What a joke. Stay far, far away.

name: L Broadhurst
snippet: This cafe is confusing, when you walk in it seems like you have to order at the counter but it‚Äôs actually table service. Also this establishment does not have public wifi..

name: Sharon
snippet: I ordered scrambled eggs on toast with a soy latte. The scrambled eggs cost $15 and regular soy latte was $5.50. I enjoyed the coffee very much and would come back again for the coffee. However, I think that the scrambled eggs is a bit overpriced and expensive for what it is. It was tasty but it was a very very light meal for me. I was expecting a bit more considering it cost $15, but I received one slice of toast with scrambled eggs.

name: Natalia Rios
snippet: Breakfast was alright. The best that they had is the French toast. The bad: the hostess had a massive attitude and had to wait for 45 mins for a table.

name: Maximiliano Mennella
snippet: Good coffee and food but cheaper options around.

name: Luna
snippet: Love the coffee, brunch and vibe here. Always good to enjoy a chat with friends.

name: Luisa Santos
snippet: Good coffee and food

name: S C
snippet: batch brew 5 starsthe pasta on their menu 5 stars

name: Dylan Bone
snippet: Such a cool place and really good food.

name: Mark
snippet: Delicious food and great coffee. One of the best in Surry Hills

name: Keh Feyy
snippet: Love the banana bread, the chicken sandwich was too heavy due to having too much cheese in it

name: Hakan T.
snippet: Single O has been roasting and brewing coffee for the past 18 years, and is no surprise they're the father of single origin coffee in Sydney. The staff are very friendly and knowledgeable. There is a large selection of beans to choose from, so there is bound to be something that you're palate will love. To keep you buzzing at home they also have subscriptions available on their website to have coffee sent regularly to your front door. They also make an incredible effort to clean and protect our environment so you can help save the world one coffee at a time.

name: Steve Grantham
snippet: It's unfair to judge an entire cafe based on a single coffee, so I won't. Instead I'll talk about the food I was going to have. Salmon salad I think, although judging by the description on the menu it may have been anything. Moved to outside when my late for the morning friend arrived because she considered the inside a covid hot spot. And fair enough. We sat outside and were released from waiter service. Not so much that I didn't get approached by such a server outside with an EFTPOS machine and a $5.50 fee for the above-mentioned coffee. 50c trail fee? Maybe if the coffee tastes good, IDK. Single O.... SMS more like. Asked if I might get a bacon and egg roll, was advised no, I couldn't order a bacon and egg roll. Fair enough. I've worked in retailing for 30 plus years and I often turn away opportunity to make money. It just makes sense..

name: Shamsul Mohdnasir
snippet: Great spot to have a coffee in the morning. A nice vibe and their coffee's are great!Food: 5/5 | Service: 5/5 | Atmosphere: 5/5 ‚Ä¶More

name: Adrian Lee
snippet: Food: 4/5 | Service: 5/5 | Atmosphere: 5/5More

name: Sasha Matheeuwsen
snippet: Have been here a couple of times now and it is one of the best places for breakfast or lunch I know of in this area.The service is superb and the food amazing, as well as the coffees.I would absolutely recommend going here for a good and fulfilling meal.

name: Jeremy Sedley
snippet: The kings of coffee.

name: Dan S
snippet: Single O provides some excellent coffee with some tasty brunch dishes. The flat white was a little disappointing, but I did have high expectations. The filter coffee tasting was well worth it and included quite different beans. The chicken toastie was awesome!

name: Zac Bautista
snippet: Typically pretentious and hipster but that‚Äôs how you know the coffee will be good I guess. The breakfast is also top quality.

name: Patrick Teo
snippet: Fantastic bacon egg burger! Everything came together very well and balanced. The cappuccino was smooth but prob has too much milk

name: Jason boogahwoogah
snippet: It was good.

name: Harry Hariyanto
snippet: Always the good vibe, food and coffee that keep you coming for them.Food: 5/5 | Service: 5/5 | Atmosphere: 5/5 ‚Ä¶More

name: Ryan Jay (Phoenixangel)
snippet: This review is specifically for the avo show. The salmon zucchini was not too great, review below. The avo show was in a word BRILLIANT. The sour dough, crumps, chili oil, avo, egg, Hommus, all came together in an explosion of flavors that delighted with each bite. Doesn‚Äôt get better than this! The salmon zucchini on the other hand was just‚Ä¶ ok. The problem was using smoked salmon - it was a bit too salty and threw the balance of the dish off. The orange, zucchini, and pine nuts worked really well, but worked very hard against the overly salty fish. To be fair this was a new menu item they were experimenting with, so I won‚Äôt include it when rating this lovely place, but diner beware!

name: Rebekah Au
snippet: This dish is clever. But the bird's nest is not the hero of Cuckoo's signature dish. Dont get me wrong, I enjoyed the crispy noodle nest, bejewelled by the poached egg. It's visually stunning and adds interesting textural elements to the meal. I love a good rich golden yolk anyday, particularly when it oozes out of the nest to coat the almost wild vegetation growing underneath. But the bed of wild greens steals the show. It's just so intensely flavourful complemented nicely by light and creamy dollops of Greek yoghurt. In comparison, I feel the noodles forgot to bring anything to the flavour party. It stands awkwardly to the side being bland, not really sure what its doing there. It could've been made of crispy potatoes, fried onions or even sweet potato to counter the spicy greens - it's such a missed opportunity. I also felt the egg to salad ratio was a bit off, I think it would've been nice to have the option to add an extra egg so the dish would be less dry. Overall, "One flew over the Cuckoo's nest" is a crowd pleaser. It tastes pretty good while also being vegan and gluten free. The staff here were amazing and I made the experience much easier to have a great catch up with friends. 4.5/5 I'd come back. Vegetarian options: Vegetarian options are not second thoughts added to the menu, they are signature dishes. Kid-friendliness: Could bring kids here, or even fur babies and many people do. Wheelchair accessibility: Tables and chairs spill out onto the main walkways. No steps or barriers in sight.

name: RODERICK GAWTHROP
snippet: I‚Äôve been to this caf√© probably between 10 to 20 times, as I've just moved in to the apartments close by, so I really wanted to like this place due to its convenient location. For pretty much 90% of visits, I have waited on average 20 to 30 minutes for lukewarm coffee and the occasional food order. The owner (I think his name is Lee) has served me a few times and on each of those occasions seems completely distracted and disinterested in even greeting his customers. By far the worst experiences at this caf√© have come during the last few times, during which I‚Äôve been served by a female (forget her name). I have had to wait well over 20 minutes for a coffee each time in the morning before work, and twice I‚Äôve even seen her drop things on the ground and continue to use them. The very last time I went for a morning coffee, I was on a deadline, and after waiting again for about 15 - 20 minutes for my coffee, eventually apologised and said that I would have to come back for the coffee another time, which she agreed to, but when I went back, on the weekend with not many customers in the shop, again I had to wait over 20 minutes. After she had proceeded to serve two customers who had come in after me (and whom also had to wait quite a while) and then went off to do something else, I went and asked if she was making my coffee. She seemed to have simply forgotten me or was just going to leave me standing there waiting. I asked for a refund and left. Avoid this place and save your money! Super long wait times, poor customer service, and often cold coffee. On a positive side, the food is ok, but not enough to bring me back. If you walk down Elizabeth street, towards the city a minute or so, there are heaps of much better caf√©‚Äôs. Disappointing !!!!!

name: Henrique Pinto Leite
snippet: Simply blown away by the amazing food. Today I had the Vegan Salmon Bagel, and taste-wise it was the best vegan salmon I've ever had. It tasted scarily close to the animal (or as the staff responded: disgustingly good), and they actually managed to do that with a tomato. Because it was in a bagel with other ingredients, the slightly different structure goes unnoticed. I've never experienced such a perfect recreation of the taste of unprocessed fish before, so I was very much amazed. The Join The Club was also delicious and had excellent taste. The Mango Lassi was an interesting one: it tasted really good, but there was so much turmeric in there that I couldn't taste the mango. I think less turmeric would have done more justice to the mango. Afterwards we shared a brownie, which was both delicious and dense, so we had no regret in sharing. The vibe was cool, and the staff was down to earth as well. On the wall there were some intriguing pictures of individual animals from an animal sanctuary, so you know exactly why this eatery only serves vegan food. We'll definitely be coming back here to try out and be surprised by more of their food and drinks.

snippet: Following a comprehensive exploration of numerous coffee shops around Sydney, particularly in the Surry Hills area, since moving from Oxford, UK, Kwila is my favourite. Firstly and most importantly the coffee served here is fabulous in aroma and flavour. Additionally, observing, and listening to the owners and their staff, it is clear all share a true passion for what they do. This passion is evident as they research, source, and roast their coffee in-house. I like the unpretentious, compact, yet warm decor and inviting style evident throughout the cafe. This extends to all the staff. They are friendly, approachable, unassuming and always willing to chat. Being a avid football (soccer) fan it‚Äôs been lovely to chat and share my passion with one of the knowledgeable baristas while sipping on a lovely flat white. If you are looking for great tasting speciality coffee, in a relaxed, lovely venue look no further than this hidden gem.

The Matcha Latte was to my liking: strong and with right sweetness. I also ordered a Chocolate and Banana Muffin and loved it!
