snippet: Nice Matcha üçµ

name: Ruby Brookes
snippet: Went here for breakfast the other day and honestly my experience was very odd. I‚Äôve been coming to Reuben Hills since 2018 as it was my favourite cafe until my most recent experience. I was initially saddened to seerye was what I came to RH for so often. I understand the change from Rye to AP Sourdough as a business decision given the links between the two cafes, however the switch from chickpea/pickled onions/dill/herb oil to inferior ingredients was disappointing however I gave it a go and was not impressed, the herb crackers were particularly bad. I understand that my personal preference is just that, and normally I wouldn‚Äôt leave a bad review over a menu change I disagree with, but that wasn‚Äôt the worst part of my experience. I also ordered a malteaser milkshake that I saw the staff drinking in front of me, which particularly appalled me. From where I was sitting I could see the milkshake being made, specifically in a tall silver milkshake glass. I then saw the staff member who made it pour out a glass worth of milkshake into a water glass and set it aside. I was then served that milkshake. A few minutes later the staff member who made the milkshake handed the extra glass to a different worker who drank it in front of me. I was honestly quite offended that neither of them had the brains or awareness to reduce/consume my $10 milkshake ANYWHERE other than right in front of me‚Ä¶ like come on‚Ä¶ My girlfriend also got the mushroom burrito that was way overpriced for what it was. Another menu change that has been for the worse, a definite downgrade from the previous breakfast burrito. At least with the breakfast burrito they used to cut it half and serve it in something slightly nicer than tinfoil. The menu changes were disappointing (they are also not reflected on the website which still has the old menu) but I‚Äôve been a loyal customer for around four years and was prepared to still come back, but the whole thing with the milkshake left a sour taste in my mouth. Whatever changes have happened in the last few months since I was last there, staff and menu, have been for the worse in my opinion.

name: laura
snippet: Overpriced brunch, food was really average. Baked eggs seemed like they forgot to add anything other than the eggs. ‚ÄòFresh‚Äô orange juice came in a small jar which cost $8! Service was awful, really rude (except for the women at the door). To top it off a surcharge was added for the weekend, which is ridiculous given it‚Äôs a brunch spot and a large % of your customers would be from the weekend.

name: Wendy Ong
snippet: I would give a negative star to this cafe for their coffee if there's an option. Came here purposely for their coffee. Staff were unfriendly, no courtesy to tell you they charge extra if pay by card. Their coffee is over price for a size that is smaller than 8oz cup. Always exploring for great coffee, I don't mind paying the extra for good coffee but their coffee was tasteless, all I drink was milk, it tasted like I am drinking hot milk with sugar, you can't even taste the creamy silky milk, they can't even froth the milk properly, one of the worst coffee I had and have to pay $4.40 for it. The '3in1' sachet coffee taste better than this. I wouldn't recommend to come here for coffee.

name: Jeremy Smith
snippet: The Reuben sandwich here, I was expecting a classic, drive here out of my way to get it. It was a massive LET DOWN.... regarding the meat, let me say it was 40% fat, who wants to eats big chunks of fat? It had a few stingy strips of brisket (not wagyu). I‚Äôve been to New York, a real Reuben has more cheese, layers of meat and pickles etc. This was a tiny over priced little sandwich which wasn‚Äôt even an adequate lunch. Im just giving the facts here. I showed the waitress all the fat picked out of the sandwich - the staff didn‚Äôt care. I don‚Äôt care about price or surcharge if the portion and food is done right.

name: Justin Jeridi
snippet: Wrong opening times, it said 7:30. I went there at 7:50 and they asked me to wait outside in the cold

name: Marina Timerbulatova
snippet: Food is nice. Horrible customer service! It takes 30-40 min for food to be prepared. When I was there, it was freezing cold and I was offered place at the bar near the window which I have taken. Later on (40 min still without food) the table behind me right under the heater was empty, however I was not allowed to move there as ‚Äúwe keep it for a larger groups‚Äù. When I suggested that I sit there until a ‚Äúlarger group‚Äù arrives and move once the group needs a table I was told ‚Äúyou cannot do that, sorry‚Äù. Do not recommend that place. There are so many other options around with a better service and food.

name: Matthew S
snippet: Long wait. Luke warm, generic, mediocre coffee at $6. Not worth it.

name: Tolly Vellis
snippet: Best I can say is that the coffee doesn't taste offensive, but it is bland and uninspired. Avoid.

name: sunnycoast4558
snippet: I got the breakfast burrito and it was $14.50 + surcharge. After reading the reviews and seeing the price I had high expectations... it was average, why is it $14.50? It‚Äôs just a burrito with some egg and sauce.... I also noticed When I was reading the menu it said add avocado $6.... that is the most expensive avocado I‚Äôve ever seen in any cafe in my life. Infact I think they might hold the record for most expensive avocado.

name: t t
snippet: I went to this cafe yesterday.The coffee was terrible. I ordered soy latte, the form was too much and espresso was so weak.

name: Mario Parussini
snippet: $24 for a coffee, a hot chocolate (which tasted like dirt) and a banana bread. When I questioned the price the staff shrugged and didn‚Äôt even let me see the splits of how much each item cost. I get you guys have a cool vibe but that shouldn‚Äôt get in the way of being nice and helpful to a customer who just handed over a premium for three items that any other mum and pop cafe would serve for half the price with a big smile.

name: Karthik Sampanni
snippet: I am not sure why this place is rated 4 stars. 1. It's in someone's double garage almost literally. You have to traverse some sights and smells to get here. 2. Most staff who work here are categorically supercilious. 3. Coffee is "ok" on best of days. It does have a non-organic, slight chemical after taste to it. It is a 4/10 compared to coffee in Italy, 5/10 overall. Of late these people are "bending their customers over" by forcing you to bring your own cup. Rather than giving you a discount for bringing your own cup, they add 50 cents by default if you don't. 4.Food is very average. Nothing healthy, mostly dense calorie stuff that tastes good with real regret later. 5. Pricing is off the charts. Coffee (Strong large FW) and basic Toast set me back $13.60. Anywhere else $8 maybe $9 with better coffee of course. Worst of all- the general arrogance thinly veiled by forced dignity is palpable. I'd be ok with all of this had this been a Michelin star restaurant. Honestly, this is just a dingy joint with BS exposed bricks to give it the hipster feel. In conclusion, the very fact that this establishment thrives is an indictment of the mellenial outlook. I am 35 (in 2019 for reference). Please visit this joint pay $25- $30 for coffee and lunch, while the pretentious workers with piercings and tattoos waddle around.. moping how the world doesn't recognise pure gold. Enjoy the nice decor of some weird 10feet alleyway with rubbish. Cheers

name: Paing Phyo Tun
snippet: Hugely disappointed and would not come back again. It was better many years ago. Now is too pricey and doesn‚Äôt taste as good, especially value point. I expect to receive higher quality food and more variety in my plates for prices you charged.

name: Info Abe-Sara
snippet: Really disappointing service. The food is fine, but there is a particularly surly and unpleasant waitress who worked today at the cafe. She refused to seat the 2 of us on a 3 seater small table - even though the cafe was empty and closing in 30 mins! We told her would go elsewhere if we couldn‚Äôt get a table and basically told us to leave. It‚Äôs a shame in today‚Äôs Sydney‚Äôs crowded Cafe landscape where service is paramount you have employees that really shouldn‚Äôt be working in the industry. Avoid this place if you would like your service to match the food!

name: MATTIA COZZI
snippet: we ordered an espresso and, besides the fact that they charged us 4$ for their local brew, we received something that was similar to a short LONG BLACK..the coffee barely had a taste and it basically felt like drinking hot water with an hint of coffee. I really don't understand all this hype for this caf√®; I guess people would rather pay for the hipster setting rather than the coffee itself!

name: Alexander
snippet: unbelievably unsympathetic Expensive prices and don‚Äòt forget the ‚Äûextras‚Äú... +10% on weekends +20% on public holidays +1,56% on card transactions - no splitbills - no variations ... wow! How arrogant and greedy can a single coffee shop act? And their coffee was not even outstanding.... Spoiled place. No recommendation.

name: Wendy Li-Wilson
snippet: Let me just state that my review has nothing to do with the food but more the way we were treated when we visited with our puppy. We waited in line for a table and told them specifically we needed to be seated with our dog. Eventually after a lengthy wait (which we are ok with as we didn't mind waiting for a dog friendly table) we got directed to the table out the back right next to their roller door. Our pup was well behaved and quickly fell asleep under the table at our feet out of everyone's way.. About 3/4 of our way through the meal a random waitress walked by and spotted him sitting there and says quiet rudely to my partner "mate, you can't have your dog in here, people are eating you have to tie him up outside." We were obviously surprised as one, we had waited for a dog friendly seat had we not? And two, at her ridiculously rude attitude. So my partner left the rest of his food to go tie our pup by a pipe near the door and sat with him as he would have only been a few months old at the time he would have gotten quite stressed if we left him alone. The waitress came round again and saw my partner sitting with my pup on the floor and goes "can't you just leave him there!?" my partner goes on to explain that he couldn't as he would cry and disturb other people. We would have been fine to go elsewhere if told up front that they weren't pet friendly instead of getting mixed messages from different people and made to feel like we did the wrong thing! What terrible customer interaction!! I will never go back based on this experience and advise anyone else hoping to take their dog with them to avoid this place

name: Carlos Vega
snippet: I have been charged $20 for Public Holiday fees... and $6 for Sunday fees... This is ridiculous especially when the staff is asking you to leave because you are taking too long on a table. And to complete since when baked eggs and fried chicken is considered South American food! Not going there anymore

name: Matthew Alba
snippet: Didn‚Äôt take my keep cup and burnt my coffee Reply: Hi Karina thank you for your reply. The coffee doesn‚Äôt matter I drink it for strategic work purposes. Maybe you should look into a supplier for your take away cups that aren‚Äôt using single use plastic.

name: Linda Lee
snippet: Dined at Reuben Hills cafe. I had one of their dishes with sourdough and chorizo, along with a Ginger & Turmeric Almond Latte. Food and coffee were delicious. About 10-15 minutes after finishing the meal and leaving the cafe I had a terrible stomachache. I immediately went to the bathroom and let it all out. The last thing I had eaten was the meal from Reuben Hills. Obviously upset about paying for a meal that made me sick, I posted on their Facebook wall informing them of what had happened and suggested that they should check their hygiene. I posted my comment, checked that it had successfully posted on the wall (it had). I happened to go back to the page a few minutes later and the post was gone! I thought that was strange so I posted it again. Checked that it had posted correctly (it had), then again, went back to check again in a few minutes. Again it was gone!!! So in response I posted another post which was a message to Reuben Hills/ their Facebook admin telling them what I thought of them. And surprise surprise, that post didn‚Äôt make it to the wall. I have been to Reuben Hills before and quite liked the food and the atmosphere. However, I‚Äôm sad to say that I will most definitely not return. Not because there was something wrong with the food (mistakes happen), but because of the way they handled it. Unbelievable.

name: Emily S
snippet: Love the coffee but it's a travesty they use minor figures oat milk (the worst kind of liquid there is)

name: Trent Evans
snippet: Staff came across rude. Left us standing at the front door ignoring us. Hard to get anyone' attention and it wasn't very busy. Food seemed overpriced for what it was. Their target audience seems to be hipsters so if that's you're thing, you'll like it.

name: Yolanda Kerr
snippet: Really disappointing - went for breakfast was shocked when my plate came out with one small piece of toast and smashed avo for $14. Service was not the best. Asked for a poached egg as a side but told they don't do poached eggs. 1.5% surcharge for using your card (not just amex). Not returning.

name: Keiran Ramirez
snippet: Overpriced, average coffee. They don't offer substitute sugar for diabetics or those on special diets which is a shame. A regular coffee is a bit bigger than a piccolo size. Joke.

name: BL
snippet: Bad service and equally bad food. Avo on rye toast was a baby sized meal and costed 14 dollars. Highway robbery and not an innovative menu. Save your money and go to the other cafes on the street.

name: Daniel Everlien Berardo
snippet: On the 22nd of October, my friend and I had breakfast at Reuben Hills and both of us had high expectations. We had the Dirty Bird and the Salmon Kokoda. The Dirty Bird was a chicken burger, and you cant really go that wrong with a burger right? But it was disgusting, from the bun which had way too much coriander to the choice of the ingredients which did not match at all with the chicken - could not even eat half of it. Secondly, the Salmon Kokoda, was essentially an extremely overpriced salad (yes salad - was rather surprised about that) with almost no salmon inside - the dish itself was also too watery and the flavours were just not matching with each other. We spent an incredible $55 for two dishes, a coffee and a pot of tea. We were still hungry and on top of that we felt disgusted by the food and we ended up eating cake at K√ºrt≈ësh - a bakery which never disappoints.

name: Simon Paw
snippet: Sadly not worth the 30 minute wait. The Not so Rebeun sandwhich was boring and overpriced. Tasteles, basically just mayo coleslaw and a couple of chunks of dry beef on some bread. Really could of done with some mustard and pickles for some kind of flavour. I would compare it to eating a piece of cardboard. Portion was tiny as well which didn't really bother me because I just wanted the experience to be over. Really disappointed. Definitely would not return.

name: Johan Mel
snippet: Horrible, rude service and average food! Advertised online as a Central/mostly South American cafe, I don't like chilli and can't eat it, I ordered Eggs with chorizo, in SA (where I lived) Ranchero or eggs are not spicy!! I asked if the chorizo was spicy and was told no but I had no reason to think eggs were spicy. I had a taste and could not have a second bite, politely explained and returned the eggs untouched to be changed for a toast. This guy with a baseball cap ("Tea" or something) comes with my small toast (no cutlery or napkins which I had to get myself) and a really aggressive and rude attitude saying that he will charge me full because most of their food is spicy and they don't need to mention it in the menu. Is not cheap, the actual cost of the food is probably 25% of the price so one is mostly paying for good service just to be treated like rubbish. Tea (or whatever ur name is) get some f manners!!

name: Briged Diaz-collian
snippet: Worst food I have ever eaten in my life. I got the tex mex sandwich it was stale two thick slices of bread with a tiny mini slice of steak in each side. Disgusting $65 for bread with hardly any steak and the French toast wasn't any better, shake and a drink. Can't believe it.

name: Brent Vile
snippet: Ordered 3 coffees. 1 of them was the correct order. If the mocha that I didn't want wasn't so offensively bitter I would have let it slide without an obnoxious google review...

name: Jodie Green
snippet: They didn‚Äôt think to let me know of their closing time when I ordered a coffee for $4.50 but when I was 2 sips in I was given the bill and then minute by minute updates of how long left until they close. I didn‚Äôt even get to finish my coffee, such a waste!

name: Abe MacDonald
snippet: Been coming for three years. Came in on Thu for a working lunch with a colleague. Three spare tables at the front and staff told us we need to go to the share table or a bench. Took a seat, then asked again could we sit at the table coz the bench wasn't working and got told "no" . Asked if we could talk to the supervisor and told "he's not here" . So, we left. Staff didn't seem to care. Mental note - Cross this place off the list for working lunches.

name: LA Peck
snippet: Disappointed! I had heard such good things and was looking forward to the visit. Farthest thing from a Reuben ever. The Reuben sandwich would be embarrassed to have your version as it's namesake. Tough, not cooked slowly or long enough, dry, nasty meat masquerading as brisket on the sandwich today. Could not even cut the meat with a fork. Will not recommend and if I had been there in different company would have sent it back.

name: Zara-Jane Lee
snippet: Unfortunately I ordered the Reuben Sandwich that was full of fat and hardly any meat. The waitress didn't seem bothered when I complained and didn't offer any compensation. Terrible customer experience. Won't be going back!

name: Adal B
snippet: I was looking forward to having a good breakfast there.I ordered coffee cake with mascarpone.It was very pricy for a slice of loaf cake.the mascarpone tasted off and was really grainy and split.I didnt it at all and told the waiter but they still charged me full price.never go back.

name: T mail
snippet: Service was terrible, Once sitting my down and taking my coffee order, waitress never returned to take my food order.So I finished the basic coffee waited for awhile and left.

name: Christopher Haigh
snippet: They charge about three different surcharges that are all ridiculous. ‚ÄúWeekend‚Äù is not a reason to jack your prices 11.5%. Coffee was luke warm.

name: Dave C
snippet: The girl who makes the coffee is very rude and does not respond when you speak to her. I do not recommend this site. Terrible serviceüò°

name: Adore B
snippet: I used to like this place. But then they introduced a 10% surcharge on weekends AND a 1.5% credit card fee. They also refuse to split bills. It's a shame, but I'm voting with my feet and won't be visiting again.

name: Jason Romain
snippet: Disappointing and expensive...ordered the broken egg which is a crab and egg burger but there was so little crab unlike last time, where there was a different roll, more crab and clearly better value for $, my partner had the huevos diforciados, eggs were overcooked, and served on a China plate chipped..and not in a cute recycled way...not amused

name: Me and Chelin
snippet: The experience didn't meet my expectations. Terrible service. I couldn't even place my order because I was completely ignored by the staff.

name: Phanthala Somchanmavong
snippet: I went to get coffee more time, but today I went there I got my wrong coffee and very slowly for take a way, I‚Äôm waiting 15 minus for coffee. When I ask for my order, staff siad wait for a queue, they just did for dine in frist, don‚Äôt care take a way

name: Cameron Phillips
snippet: Poorly pulled espresso at high prices. If style and a moustache is more important than substance then this is your place.

name: Mick O'Connor
snippet: Great to see that the position of the chairs were so much more important than the needs of the customer. You have a lot to learn, try looking outside of your small world

name: Eric Dimech
snippet: Service = terrible.There‚Äôs annoying busy cafe slow service that is somewhat understandable and then there‚Äôs just plan ol‚Äô terrible.

name: Pepe C
snippet: $14.50 for one piece of avocado toast...ummm try again sweetie.

name: philippa ell
snippet: Came to buy a take away coffee, had to order at the counter, then as soon as I handed over my money I got told to go wait outside. Rude!

name: Robert Clark
snippet: Food is ridiculously overpriced... $20 for a little burger. Definitely not worth it!!

name: Remy Hung
snippet: Poor service. The staff has no idea what they are doing. Clearly overrated

name: Misha Bach
snippet: Pretty bad service, rude staff and average food.

name: Natasha Stokes
snippet: Went in thinking the avo on toast was $13 because of their online menu and it turned out to be $18.00 instead for a small slice of sour dough with avocado and cherry tomatoes on it. The coffees were also marked up by 50c and their ‚Äúregular‚Äù size was absolutely pathetic and even smaller than a normal cafe‚Äôs ‚Äúsmall‚Äù size for coffee. There was nothing special about the food or coffee at all. Terrible. All i can say is that some Sydney people are crazy!!!

name: Ryan Andreasen
snippet: Rushed to leave the table whilst still drinking our coffee. Was asked to give up the table after 1 hour 20 minutes whilst still drinking our coffee in order to make a place for a table of 4. No reservation, and plenty of other places they could have sat. We'd purchased 2 meals and ordered 3 drinks. When told we had to vacate the table in 10 minutes, we were asked to leave just 5 minutes later. Waitress with ginger hair picks up the unfinished coffee to remove it from the table without asking. The pure pursuit of money was obvious. We come to Paramount a lot, but not anymore.

name: Xu Cheng Shi
snippet: After waiting close to 20 minutes after my partner's dish was brought out, they served me COLD fried chicken and STALE waffles. This was disappointing especially as the explanation from staff was that they had many delivery orders to fulfill and were short staffed. I can understand post lockdown period chaos in the hospitality industry but quality control standards should at the very least be upheld - especially after waiting much longer for the food that usual. They did offer to remake the dish but given that my partner had already finished her meal at that stage, it didn't seem appropriate to wait another 25+ minutes for them to remake mine. Ultimately, I opted for a refund of my dish. What was particularly striking was the manager in charge explained the staff shortages but also rudely remarked that I should 'have some patience'. This was not an attitude to expect from staff shortly after serving cold fried chicken. Overall, the experience left quite a bitter taste in our mouths especially as the prices were also quiet steep even in comparison to it's brunch contemporaries. I think it's safe to say, we will not be returning customers.

name: agnes agnes
snippet: Foods are great, however the service is not really good. We were queueing up and waiting for one of the staff to place us on a table but no staffs bother to respond to us despite we called them numerous times. When we finally saw an empty spot, since no one is on our front line we sat down and asked the staff. The staff however called us to stand up and go back to queue only to end up sitting at the same spot. Me and my friend are ordering 2 coffees and chicken burger for myself, and my friend still need time to order her food. Later after my friend order her food, her food came earlier than another food because the staff forgot to input my order. When we were eating, a staff asked us to move seats and at this point we are already pretty bummed. When I was going to order coffee again, it seems that all staffs are ignoring and pretending not to see until I stood up and gestured to order (we also saw other people experienced this and they look pretty frustrated). When we are paying the meal, the bill says 57, but on the card machine it is 58.6 and I asked why is it 58.6. Turns out she forgot to input the surcharge notice on the bill (this is basic knowledge for every cashier) and she insisted that I was wrong for questioning her, even when her senior is telling her to input the surcharge. We were not pleased with this attitude, the food is great but please improve the service quality and give them more training.

name: Richie Johnson
snippet: Overall pretty disappointing in a lot of ways. We first sat down outside as we had a dog and we were waiting for our friends to arrive, one pregnant and another with a pram. A larger family arrived and the waitress moved us away and onto the street tables and told us that they had arrived first. We explained we had been sitting waiting to which she told us that she had she had seen them arrive first and we would have to move. Im not sure how they could have arrived first if we were seated already!! another lady even commented later to us how unfairly we had been treated. After this, it just got worse. she was abrupt and kept reminding us that we couldn't split bills which we had acknowledged countless times. The coffee was cold as was the food. There was a stalk in my bacon and egg roll. I can quite easily say an underwhelming experience at best and it all seems to be overhyped and poorly executed. Give me a small cafe with good food any day of the week over this. I won't be coming back

name: Ange Mack
snippet: Had brunch here on Saturday with friends and found it quite disappointing. Coffee was terrible, food was fine and the service was below average. Felt like we were being rushed to order, eat and pay. It was obvious that a high turn over was more important than good customer service.

name: Jacob Patterson
snippet: Ordered a coffee before a meeting and after waiting for no less than TWENTY FIVE minutes for a coffee, I had to leave and was chased no less than 300 meters by the waiter who asked why I hadn‚Äôt paid for the coffee that never came. What a joke.

name: Saam R1
snippet: I cant believe this place has received an above 4 rate. We were told we'll be seated in 25 min (which is a rough estimate I get it) but we waited more than 45. This is not the worst part. When you wait 45 min staring at a menu, one simple thing you expect is your order to be taken immediately after you sit and receive an apology for the unexpected long wait. We clearly had enough intimate time with the menu. But after a lot of waiting we are told that you should wait another couple of mins for your order to be taken and with some weird attitude from the waiter. Are we a joke to you? Plus, the place has so much space and even empty tables without seats but they like their customers to waste time waiting. Seemingly respect to customers is not a thing in this place. .

name: Wen Jia Liu
snippet: I can only comment on the coffee served here. I ordered a cold brew and it tasted more like a long black with ice. Moreover, the coffee was acidic to the point where as it hit the back of my throat, it had a distinctive vomit flavour. I've had a lot of cold brew/drip coffees, and I can say with confidence that this was simply awful. My girlfriend's cappuccino wasn't any better - it was milky and lacking in flavour.

name: Wiremu Crawford
snippet: I visited this place about 6 months ago and ordered the gumbo and the dish came out cold but with warm chicken. I didn't know that it wasn't meant to be like that. I got bad food poisoning that lasted 2 weeks and ever since that day my stomach has not been the same. I'm now suffering with bouts of IBS that I've never experienced in my life: be more careful about your food hygiene! Would've never expected a place with raving reviews to screw me over so bad.

name: Matthew Early
snippet: Paramount was at one point a favourite breakfast spot of mine. The food was interesting, the vibe was energetic and the coffee was smooth. However, after a recent visit I left feeling highly disappointed and doubting wether I will go back. I found the food to be extremely overpriced for what was delivered and lacked the inspiration that you would expect considering the price tag.

name: Mitch
snippet: The coffee had an interesting taste which was nice but I wouldn't want to drink more than once. The food was ridiculously overpriced. The cafe demands $10 minimum purchase before allowing EFTPOS/credit payment and you are not advised of this until after you've placed your order. I believe there's no excuse for this; it's very greedy practice and as a result of this policy I will never return.

name: adam neylon
snippet: Came in with high hopes. Was let down and dissapointed. First of all, the staff member who served us was extremely cold and unwelcoming. Left to go find our own table, we took a seat at what felt more like a table for hobbits. We tried to move the small chair out of the corner and around to the other side of the table and was told we can't because it's a fire hazard?? Our coffees came out and my long black tasted disgusting. A pale, single-colour crema on top, with a bitter taste. My friend's latte wasn't much better. Our food came and it was actually quite tasty and well-presented - the only part I liked about the whole experience. The rude waitress paraded back and took our empty plates and cups with no comment about how our meals were. We went to pay and she just said "$31.70" (or something I can't remember the exact price). What happened to some good old small talk to make the customer feel appreciated? Anyway, won't be coming here again.

name: Bonny Morlak
snippet: 5 stars for the guys making coffee 1 star for the seater and server. Cold, impatient and borderline cold. Feeling unwelcome

name: Sam Raworth
snippet: Came here this morning for breakfast with a friend, firstly we were seated at the bar where we werent greeted by a waitress. I ordered scrambled eggs on toast and a side of potatos, we waited for the food to come, it came no problem except i only got my side of potatos?! i didnt mention anything for about 10mins before i asked a waitress about my food she went off to check, didnt come back. A second waitress came back, asked if i had my food, by the time i got my food 20mins had passed my friend had already finished, so i was left eating my breakfast awkwardly, also nobody asked how my food was. (Good job i wasnt in a rush) to top it off when we left nobody said thank you and goodbye.

name: Andr√©s P√©rez
snippet: Bad coffee I'm serious it was HORRIBLE! Food not great and expensive they didn''t even have tomato sauce. The staff is nice but I don't really understand why this place became that popular. I wouldn't come back.

name: Roger Lam
snippet: If the food was good then the 20% surcharge on a public holiday would be fine.Food was subpar and overpriced and the coffee was watered down with no flavour.

name: Peter Chew
snippet: I was here last week and was told at 3pm that we could not order food from the kitchen anymore as the kitchen had closed, which was fair enough even though the website stated the restaurant closed at 4pm. What really peeved me off was after telling me this the waiter then proceeded to take the FOOD ORDER of 8 girls to the table next to us! When I asked for an explanation, he said they were allowed an exception as they were in BEFORE 3pm. However if you were willing to cook 8 meals for these girls how could you not be willing to cook 2 more meals for me and my partner when we were ready to order first! In short the service and management here is DISGRACEFUL! Put it down to whatever, whether it was actually discrimination or just plain stupidity on the waiter's and supposedly managers part, this place should be avoided at all cost!

name: Danielle Jones
snippet: Did not check ours or other peoples vaccine passports and check ins when we went on Sunday, was extremely busy, but this is no excuse.

name: Andrew
snippet: Does not deserve more than 1 star, coffee is okay, nothing special. For 30% more than what you pay at other coffee shops you get half the size of a normal cup. I was really surprised to see a very small cup for a $4,50 cappuccino.

name: Roya Ekraminaghsh
snippet: The coffee was mediocre, the pastry options very limited although they are supposedly known for their donuts, and the avo on toast was probably the worst one I have ever had! Basically a piece of toast with a ton of tomatoes.

name: Aaron Chen
snippet: Can't do booking so stupid. We walked in and the staff told us to wait for 1 hr.

name: Chris R
snippet: Great place for meetings - BUT no access to the WiFi? Why??? Are you the only cafe in Sydney without access to WiFi when 80% of your patrons during the week are using your premises for work. This is really not good :(

name: Super Jonno
snippet: They served me half a sausage with scrambled eggs that had way too much garlic and onions. No thanks

name: Emily S
snippet: Loved this place until they started using Minor Figures (please go back to Oatly! I miss it)

name: Yufeng Lin
snippet: Without being given a menu, I ordered 2√ó Cappuccino and 1√ó Banana Bread but charged $23 last Sunday. After checking their website, I found banana bread is only $8, that means I was overcharged by $6! Very bad impression on this caf√©!

name: Kalvin Chung
snippet: Ordered fried chicken on waffles this morning. Waffles were very dry and the chicken tasted like leftovers

name: Shahrzad Kamali
snippet: Horrible service, after we have been waiting for 45 min to get seat, we wait another 5 min to find some one to come and get order without any apologise. It was unbelievable. And the attitude of staff was terrible. Horrible experience for the weekend morning. :(

name: Rick Schaeffers
snippet: Some of the most creative and delicious food I've had in a while, but the no split bills and surprise surcharge left a bitter taste.

name: Samuel O'Shannessy
snippet: This place had good reviews, but I dont like paying for bad food, so I am leaving this. No sympathy from the waiter

name: Jack Cox
snippet: Most overrated experience. The coffee was undrinkable, the menu was some sort of attempt at comedy, I believe. Won't be even contemplating returning.

name: Adrian Grabicki
snippet: Obnoxiously bad service and mediocre, overpriced food. With hundreds of cafes nearby, I'm surprised this place stays open.

name: lucy i
snippet: The atmosphere is nice but the food was really disappointing :(

name: Benjamin Smee
snippet: Tries so hard to be cool that it's unable to serve anything resembling a normal meal

name: Eden Pigram
snippet: Cool vibe, let down by the rudeness of some staff

name: Mac Pinto
snippet: Very hippie and hipsters bad quality.

name: ed28
snippet: 7 eleven $1 coffee

name: Ka√Øa
snippet: Asked for poched eggs, refused..

name: Tameka McKenzie
snippet: Disorganised is an understatement. After finding a cafe with no name, we were seated, and the staff were friendly enough, just not very helpful. We wanted 2 takeaway coffees, we did not realise that the take away section was seperate to the main area, which the lady was fine with ordering takeaways. Although all we ordered was a large flat white on zymill, and a large cap on soy. Only to be informed you apparently you only do one type of milk though so normal dairy it was. First it took 3 attempts to remember the two coffees. Then 2 coffees came to our table that weren't for us. Which caused more confusion. Finally we got our takeaway order, only the cap was small not large. Whatever I can deal with that, probably a good thing considering it was dairy. Then spent what felt like 10 mins trying to pay, but no body seemed to be interested in helping. Finally we were leaving with what was hoped to be bloody good coffees. And as we walked past the take away section, what do I see. Bloody Soy milk! This would have been ok if we didn't end up throwing out both coffees, two sips in and all mine tasted like was warm milk. Sorry, but you had great reviews and we were excited for some good coffee, and maybe we confused you. But we weren't impressed.

name: Christian Dimichiel
snippet: To start I‚Äôd like to credit them on the atmosphere of the cafe. However the lady assigning tables was out right rude and passive aggressive- my dad made a joke about me being impatient she then said ‚Äúdoes it run in the family‚Äù in a very un inviting tone. I would suggest she lightens up or steps up out of the heat

name: B C
snippet: I had heard that this place was good. It is definitely not. Overpriced horrible food. I got the chicken toastie for $17.50z it was the most disgusting sandwich I had ever had. The chicken was mostly pink, I‚Äôm not sure if that‚Äôs the way the chicken is supposed to be? But it was like eating canned spam chicken and after my first bite due to the pinkness of the chicken I became worried about food poisoning from uncooked chicken. This place should be ashamed of themslelf and if I get food poisoning they will be hearing from me. Don‚Äôt waste your money or time. They should stick to coffee not food. I took photos of the chicken as well just in case.

name: Nicolle Milosevich
snippet: Ordered a large Chai latte and latte $9.50. Took 25 minutes to receive. The barista forgot or missed the two large cups in front of her for our drinks, no apology. Had 5 tables sitting and we were first to order coffee from a group of 5 waiting for takeaway. No organisation. Wont be returning.

name: Chris Kostakis
snippet: Considering the great food options available on the street, Single O is not up to snuff. The meatloaf was nothing but glorified spam and the brisket roll was just reheated oily meat that left a terrible after taste. Save yourself the time and idegestion and go to The Sandwich Shop a few doors down instead.

name: Zhi Y
snippet: Disappointed with the coffee as came here twice over 3 weeks and the coffee was weak, quite acidic and watered down, almost as though the coffee grounds had been reused and the milk was watered down. My friend who has their coffee said hers was lukewarm and disappointed as well

name: jonathan humphry
snippet: Hated the place. It's unfortunate 2minutes from my house. I gave them chance after chance. Finally after 4 stupid mistakes with my order over 4 different days. Sorry. No more chances. My friends who I took there one really made me feel embarrassed. Heavily embarrassed

name: o
snippet: Very rude Blond waitress. We just have to walk away.

name: J C
snippet: The flat white was blend and way toooo hot, which was not drinkable. This place is overrated.

name: William Chang
snippet: Really bad service. Been waiting and standing for nearly an hour, put me on list twice kept asking if I am waiting for a table. Arranged table for people who was there later than me. No organized at all. Will never visit again.

name: Chu Chu
snippet: We arrived first, but late to advanced

name: Rob Weston
snippet: Coffee was terrible!!!Paid over $10 for 2 coffees.Ridiculous!!

name: popatk
snippet: Looks shut down now. Piles of newspapers on the floor, graffiti on external Walls.

name: Owen Paulson
snippet: Overpriced, disorganised and rude.

name: Liam D
snippet: Worst place ever

name: lee ping Chong
snippet: Burnt bacon

name: Jessica Bait
snippet: Booooo

name: Khanh Nguyen
snippet: Duck salad was okay but not filling, and my eggs on toast were poached a bit tooo well

name: Andrej Stevanovic
snippet: Ordered coffee at carriageworks from these guys Waited 20 minutes All attitude and no care Save yourself aggravation and don‚Äôt get coffee there on Saturdays

name: pink mint
snippet: It's not my coffee type. but sigleO is best coffee shop in sydney

name: Daniel Augustine
snippet: I work in the area but was not a fan of this place. I met a colleague who was having breakfast and I wasn't. However the staff became a little 'in your face' until I ordered something (I had 3 different people pushing for an order). My colleague then asked if she could get her breakfast in a takeaway container so that once she has finished her coffee we could leave, they then said they refused to take the order at the table and if she wanted it to takeaway she'll have to go up and pay (unnecessarily complicated if you ask me) They also got her order wrong so once she got back to the office it was too much of a mission to go back and sort. Apparently her coffee was pretty good however so maybe worth it for that? In a place where there are so many good coffee places, they need to step up their service levels to stand out. However this is only my opinion and others will likely have had different opinions. But service is important to me.

name: Benjamin Humphrey
snippet: Coffee and food is good but this cafe has the most disorganized and distracted group of staff I've come across. They were quite busy on Sunday, so we had to wait about 15 mins. Fair enough. We got seated and waited another 10 minutes before we had to ask someone for menus. The person we asked for menus didn't want to take our order for coffee, so we further waited for someone else to come back. We eventually ordered coffee and food. It all arrived at different times; coffees one by one. After eating we eventually managed to order another round of coffee but they messed up the order, giving us a chai latte instead. 1.5 hours later we settled the bill and one waiter apologized, saying how busy it was, and gave us the last round of coffees on the house. So that made up for it a little, hence two üåü instead of one!

name: Metti herjou
snippet: Great coffee, nice out-door seats, pleasant atmosphere BUT unfortunately the menu is VERY limited and pricy. Couldn't make any changes, she said "Not an Option". Which not customer friendly.

name: Charlie Miso
snippet: Quick coffee to go whilst in the area before a tender briefing. Just beat the rush but got served last. Seems if you're drinking buddies with the staff, or a regular you get priority. Us normal folk have to wait. Nothing special about the coffee. Expensive as well.

name: Fausto Brusamolino
snippet: Way too overpriced.I ordered the tempeh plate from their menu... the portion was incredibly small, and there was nothing special about it.Being vegan does not mean eating less.

name: Jin hong
snippet: my long black was pretty cold and didnt have any crema which i assume they served the one made long time ago or something if not, still very disapointing experience. used to be one of the best but not anymore

name: Brett
snippet: Good coffee. Baristas are too busy talking between each other to take orders properly making me repeat myself. This happens alot.

name: Neelan Govender
snippet: Coffee was good but not hot enough. Service and waits were not good to be completely honest.

name: Stella Ryu
snippet: Food and coffee is just nice and not more

name: Leonardo Bastian
snippet: coffee not as great as before

name: Alexandria E.L
snippet: I've heard a lot of hype in regard to Neighbourhood's coffee, and it did not disappoint. exceptional coffee, quirky little hole-in-the-wall cafe, with little seats along the path to have a quick sit while waiting for your coffee.

name: Tesspresso Melbourne
snippet: Great little hole in the wall!

name: Randy
snippet: small coffee shop but got good coffee, using artificier coffee and synesso for espresso and mahlkonig for batch brew . lovely atmosphere. too bad there was car parked in front of it so i cant get the picture from accross of the street

name: Jamie //
snippet: It's the best coffee I've had in Sydney and I've had a LOT. Staff are wicked and the roast is unreal, smooth, no bite literally never had an average cup from here.

name: James Flanagan
snippet: Believe the hype. The coffee really is THAT good. Friendly service and up there with the best coffee I've had. Would be nice if they had more food options than bagels though.

name: Michael Dalton
snippet: This would have to be the best coffee shop in Sydney. Definitely worth a visit if you are in the area. Very close to central. The coffee is consistent and the staff are great. I only wish they were open on the weekend! A must if you're a coffee lover

name: Leonardo Wilhelm
snippet: Oat milk coffee is an interesting experience, sweet and filling. Very smooth coffee, definitely a star in Sydney's competitive cafe landscape. Croissants from Penny Fours are a great treat. New venues for food and wine coming soon.

name: Keun S
snippet: One of the best coffees you can get around Surry hills, you will find delicious filter coffees, hot chocolate with house made oats milk (sooooooooooo good), great milk coffees and the banter!!!! Great guys who care about coffee and their customers.

name: Samuel Wilkie
snippet: From the coffee to the customer service. There's a reason this tiny cafe does so well. Sean is the definition of a good bloke. Always has a smile on his face and keen for a chat.

name: Alex Blaikie
snippet: Great coffee in a tiny, hole-in-the-wall coffeeshop.

name: chanho hong
snippet: This is absolutely the best coffee bar in the world. The most fantastic coffee and amazing customer service is provided. Damn good!

name: Kyle L
snippet: Unbelievably good coffee, great banter, great guys and, simply, the best coffee in the area by a mile. Does come at a bit of a cost, of course but you more than get what you pay for.

name: Tina Tsang
snippet: Great coffee ! Great service!

name: Brett O'Donnell
snippet: Best coffee I‚Äôve had in Sydney hands down. Always good service and staff are very friendly.

name: Benjamin Pulley
snippet: A literal hole-in-the-wall, seek the place out for local color and charming owners. Expertly crafted coffee, but the winner might be the hot chocolate.

name: Dan Stewart
snippet: Cool place, nice guys, and the oat milk was a pretty cool twist I hadn't seen before! Will have to try the hot chocolate next! Thanks guys!

name: wu yan
snippet: I like the pear Danish and hot chocolate. It is a wonderful breakfast for me. The cup of hot chocolate is so cute. üòã

name: Franz Wiebe
snippet: Coffee professionals serving great coffee with super friendly service... With Sydney's best baristas this is the place to go!

name: T G
snippet: The best looking barista in Sydney, doesn't make a bad coffee either.

name: Dina Patarcic
snippet: Love the coffee here! My almond flat white was delicious

name: Tim Heywood
snippet: Charlie and the lads at neighbourhood have got a brilliant little spot. So nice to drop by and enjoy delicious coffee in the sun.

name: Phil George
snippet: Awesome coffee. Awesome staff. Awesome design. My favourite coffee in Sydney.

name: Jidde Jacobi
snippet: Basic place, but decent coffee (I ordered the batch brew). Unfortunately they only served coffee in takeaway cups, even though I asked for a mug. Bit unnecessary plastic. Not gonna save the world with these guys.

name: J Ga
snippet: Typical hipster service - preferential treatment for known customers and general uncaring attitude Unknowledgeable baristas - just the country of origin (and price) provided Coffee - lacked any subtlety of flavor Espresso - first sip was the only redeeming quality. Very rich, smooth and creamy. Ended up quite watery though. Overall a very disappointing experience for what is *supposed* to be one of the better roasters in Sydney *Added note: at least 4-5 flies buzzing around inside while trying to sit and enjoy made the whole experience even worse

name: Azmi Badres
snippet: The coffee was good but man, coming from Melbourne where most barista are super friendly.. the guys here are so coocky except for one dude he was cool. I felt that they looked down on me n so are my friends also felt the same.Not a reviewer but this place deserves one

name: Benny Scarcelli
snippet: Promising according to the rumours and looks. Unfortunately this was a disappointing coffee experience for an Italian born coffee lover: no go! I would have expected such an average product from an average cafe, definitely not from a place that claims to be a specialty coffee bar and serves you a glass of water with your espresso (short black) like in Italy. The build up before drinking the coffee was a 10 on 10 if only you were not just about to find out your palate is tasting a non pleasuring burnt coffee with a souring acidity and aftertaste.

name: Sam Bailey
snippet: Coffee is great but have come here multiple times with really rude staff. Head up the road instead to Royale Speciality on Crown St - coffee is amazing and the staff are super friendly.

name: Matthew Naismith
snippet: They do make good coffee if your worthy of being served. If you value service go somewhere else.

name: Sumith Jitta
snippet: Great coffee, but loads of attitude from the guy who took the order. Didn't even callout when the takeaway was ready.

name: Mic Donald
snippet: Over priced coffee to begin with and then a card surcharge on top. Overall experience really average.

name: Tori Kim
snippet: Staff wasn't friendly

name: Jessica Santosa
snippet: Coffee game might be near-flawless but sitting atmosphere was terrible. Or lack thereof? There was nowhere to really sit. Very 'get in, get out' sort of vibe. Staff are arrogant because they know they're good baristas. A little more humility please, and then I'll recommend you to my friends. :)

name: Joseph O'Donoghue
snippet: The coffee's good but pricey. It's new and shiney and cool and all that... But to me, pretty soulless. Sydney people seem to be attracted to that crap though. Great location, but my advice? Put some art on the damn wall. Even if it's blood red and horrible. Bring this skeleton to life. Anyone can be minimalist. But it takes guts to share your personality. Especially in this town.

name: Anda
snippet: I‚Äôve ordered 2 hot coffee takeaway (pic and cap) but I got cold piccolo and cold cappuccino instead.We drive from the countryside to this cafe because I heard it was popular but it upset me a little bit.

name: CB
snippet: Good quality coffee & nice vibe however extra 20 cent charge for using eftpos. So it's $4.70 4 coffee. Sorry guys this is not legit & an irritant 4 customers.

name: samuel griffith
snippet: Fantastic coffee and a beautiful space. Two of the staff are exceptionally rude but the owner and some of the others make up for it.

name: Andrew Harvey
snippet: Great coffee but would love to have some better food options

name: Wayne Jus
snippet: Tried two flat whites and found the waiter mute, agree with other reviewers, no soul or character, so many coffee shops in Sydney that exceed our experience here

name: Ben Barry
snippet: Great coffee but lacks atmosphere when there midweek

name: Tristan March
snippet: The coffee; Beautiful and crisp! The service; Lackluster...

name: George Maniatis
snippet: It's ok. Closes early. No toilets.

name: T mail
snippet: Basic

name: Irene
snippet: Coffee-only outlet. Great vibe, fast and friendly service and really lovely space - ample sitting space outdoors as well as indoors. The only reason I rate it four stars and not five is because the coffee was missing a kick to my taste. It is nice but not yet great. Would I come back? Absolutely, for the vibe, excellent service and a nice cup of long black.

name: Alexander The
snippet: Ordered crab cake. I asked the waiter how they serve the dish because the menu wording is way to "hipster" for me. The waiter explained to me as if I'm dumb. What I want to know was basically whether this dish is sweet or savoury and he said : "the dish has crab cake so definitely savoury". What they serve me was a tacky plating of chunky watermelon, with smashed avocado, crab cake, poached egg, and Extremely sweet cucumber jam. The only thing I enjoy was the crab cake. Very confusing dish. Coffee also average. Won't go back.

name: Nicholas Hammer
snippet: I used to come here regularly however the service has gone way down hill recently. I sat outside today with my dog and two other friends on a table of four. To put things into perspective it‚Äôs 13 degrees and windy so we all wrapped ourselves in blankets. A few minutes after sitting down the manager came to our table and demanded we hand over one of our blankets. Our friend then had a complaint regarding the size of their meal. The avocado is priced at $22.00 and a very small portion. The same manager was rude and continually interrupted and demanded to know what he wanted rather than listening and acknowledging the complaint. Rude management and poor customer service I will not be returning.

name: Jessica Clayton
snippet: Paid $40 for two plates of just two sides each (2 eggs and a handful of mushrooms). A tiny amount of food as we weren‚Äôt that hungry, but we‚Äôre charged as if we‚Äôd had eggs on toast with extras. This should be stated that we would be charged for more than what we had. Won‚Äôt be back.

name: Greer Moss
snippet: Arrived and got sent upstairs to sit at the bar as I was dining solo. Ordered a soy latte to wait 20 mins for it to come back curdled and bitter. Second attempt just as bad, seriously guys this is Sydney- learn your coffee skills! And no I dont want almond milk but thanks.

name: Judith Walker
snippet: Do not go on the basis of impeccable coffee. Coffee is expensive and one of the worst we had. Not worth the price. The staff were not attentive or caring. May be they would have been nicer if we ate but it was not lunch or breakfast and they should not have that attitude. Will not go back.

name: Preston Foster
snippet: ok i deleted my original review because my figures were incorrect. The ACCC states that eftpos should attract no more than 0.5% surcharge for recovering the actual cost of the service. AMEX about 1.5%.. You guys charge 5%.. (18 cents on a $3.50 coffee) im just pointing out that you're actually charging too much surcharge. You're the only cafe in the area that still slaps the consumers with too much surcharge. The customer isnt silly guys...

name: siren Rose
snippet: Sitting outside kinda make me feel the food will get polluted by the dust as it‚Äôs quite close to Crown Street so many cars passing by.Music is too loud just like nightclub.

name: Veronica D
snippet: Topnotch food and coffee no doubt but u do get a reminder that you have leave cos other ppl are waiting by the waitress.. Like literally asked you to pay the bill and, leave.

name: Alex Vivancos
snippet: If you could eat through Instagram breakfast would have been amazing!!More marketing than food.

name: Callum Forbes
snippet: Super slow service. Unattentive staff. One star.

name: J R
snippet: Food was very average for the price , way too much butter on the toast instead of being on the side , bacon was tasteless, eggs has a weird taste , coffee was good though but that‚Äôs about it

name: Ozden YILMAZ
snippet: The food and the service was great until I realized there were bugs in my bok choi. It is such a nice place with outside seating, good coffee; they should make sure to wash the greens thoroughly.

name: Julie Jiang
snippet: The food was okay, however the juice was literally the worst I've ever had. Can't taste much except the ginger, olive oil and mostly water... Can't believe they charged $10 for that. The staff there were friendly, asking me if i wanted another juice, while I actually prefer water.

name: Nishat N
snippet: I‚Äôve been wanting to eat at Cuckoo Callay for quite a while now but have been put off by the queue outside. I finally did line up and after about 10 minutes of waiting, was directed to the upper level where there were about 4 free tables. Not sure what‚Äôs going on there but it‚Äôs pretty annoying to have been made to wait for no reason. My friend joined me a while later, reporting a line outside. Meanwhile, there was still some space upstairs. Never mind. Then came the fact that everything (menu, ordering, paying) had to be done online. This really, really annoyed me. Both of us were forced to bring out our phones and spend a considerable amount of time essentially online shopping. The online menu was badly set out, with options under different categories meaning you had to keep going back and forth. It kept getting worse. From being charged all sorts of extra surcharges (including to use the whole online system which I absolutely did not want to!) to being asked for my name, phone number and credit card details! We were completely turned off! We hadn‚Äôt seen each other in ages and now we were on our phones for about 15mins. It definitely prevented us from ordering anything more after that meal order. People don‚Äôt go to a cafe just to eat pretty food with quirky names. They seem to understand that but also not understand it. As for the actual meal - I had the chilli eggs which were really delicious. The coffee was quite bad. Which is just as well because I didn‚Äôt feel like I missed out because I didn‚Äôt order a second one as I usually would.

name: Melissa
snippet: Had to wait a short time, then directed up stairs to an uncomfortable window seat for four of us but whoever the mic'd up hostess was talking to, didnt understand that we were a party of four & servers would walk off without taking everyone's order. Good thing my husband brought his appetite because by the time he'd read through the menu, he was quite full of word salad. The poached eggs on sourdough was nice but knife provided did not cut through the crusty bread, no other option available. A bit too pretentious for my liking, won't be going back.

name: Arthur C M3dia
snippet: Tasty bacon & egg bun ..had the same order the day before...decided to sit in the cafe as it was raining.. the sit in cafe price is almost double...shame

name: Eliza Mathews
snippet: Food is interesting and tasty, but service isn‚Äôt great. We wanted to go to this restaurant to celebrate my twin sisters‚Äô birthday. We did try calling to make a booking because we knew space for a group of 7 could be an issue here, and were told they didn‚Äôt accept bookings. We arrived early to make sure we could get a table, and lucky for us the whole outdoor area of the restaurant was available. Whilst we would have loved to sit there, they wouldn‚Äôt let us sit outside as we were a group. Instead they sat us inside at the high table, which was really tricky for eating with a baby. I hate to complain and realize it can be hard for restaurants to cater for groups, but we were really disappointed with the service and wanted to flag to anyone in a group that this isn‚Äôt the best location for them.

name: Jami Irwin
snippet: We went for Bottomless Brunch and the wait staff acted like we were a burden. They rolled their eyes at us when we politely asked for a refill for our 2 hour sitting. Poor service. The food was pretty, but heavily overpriced for the portion size.

name: Renad M
snippet: Very busy, yet food of highest quality and creativity. You can tell that both thought and effort were put into creating their menu. Seating can be a little awkward as people walk past you and so there is little room for privacy, layout could be better utilised to seat less people more spaciously and comfortably especially with COVID19 restrictions of 4 square metres which the cafe is not following.

name: Karen W
snippet: Poor waitress staff lack knowledge of the coffee menu. The filtered coffee was watery and bland. The food looked good but taste was disappointing. Poor balance of flavour. Mostly only taste the chilli or curry. Very dry quinoa/rice in the dish. Only thing good was the single origin cold brew.

name: Aleisha Kay-Pickard
snippet: Great busy atmosphere , waited for a table as the pics of food look incredible, although when we tasted our dishes, turns out the food was WAY too spicy it burnt my mouth out . My eggs were absolutely full to the brim with way too much chilli . More than the average dish !!! Not what I was hoping for being heavily pregnant, felt sick from it all the way home. Was really looking forward to eating here but was really let down . Im sorry guys I definitely won't be back . The presentation looked awesome but tasted so wrong.

name: Nicola Carretta
snippet: Coffee was alright, service wasn‚Äôt the best. Got eggs on toast which was 2 pieces of dry bread stacked on top of each other and only enough eggs to cover the top piece of toast. Other better cafes in Surry Hills, won‚Äôt be back

name: William
snippet: Average food. Small portions. Overpriced. Bad coffee.

name: Jerimy Souza
snippet: We would have liked to have given this place 4 or 5 star but unfortunately due to a staff member named Kika who weren‚Äôt too kind or even friendly to us, this had to be a 2 star rating. (abrupt and not friendly). Food, location, music, price was fine. Maybe this person had a bad morning but Kika the name of the wait staff (wearing glasses) should‚Äôve been courteous at least.

name: Igor A
snippet: Quite dissapointing really. slow service. food is only average for the price you pay. bit too oily and salty. drinks look fancy but again on the smaller size.

name: Anne Souza
snippet: Would have liked to have given this place 4 or 5 star but unfortunately due to a staff member that was rude to us (abrupt and not at all friendly) it had to be a 2 star rating. Food, location, music, price was fine. Maybe this person had a bad morning but Kika the name of the wait staff (wearing glasses) should‚Äôve been a little more courteous.

name: Colby Stevenson
snippet: $13 for granola with yoghurt and fruit.. half a cup of granola, 30mL of yoghurt, 1 strawberry, 1 raspberry, and 3 blueberries. Highway robbery.

name: chris rose
snippet: Have had good experience here in the past but the meal today was very oversalted not good experience. Initial greeting was also rude.

name: Sally Leachonson
snippet: Food was tasteless. Coffee was mediocre

name: Google Reviewer Super
snippet: Not very pram friendly unless you want to sit outdoors.

name: Hana Marra Murra
snippet: Cool looking place, very busy on public holidays. We ordered the eggs on toast with sides and coffees. The coffee was nice, the toast was good with some good relish! The scrambled eggs were presented nicely but had some sort of oil or dressing on them that made them taste really odd, and no flavouring with salt pepper or herbs. I would recommend this place but maybe more of a coffee spot or lunch spot as many of their brunch items were more lunch based instead of breakfast.

name: Erick T
snippet: The food are all alright and almost all are cooked perfectly, but there's just bit and pieces of it that we didn't like. The one flew over the cuckoo's nest taste great and nice presentation. The salmon is a nice addition though doesn't add much to the dish. No other complaints. The chicken katsu was cooked perfectly and not dry. Coating was nice and crispy. Probably the only disappointing element was the curry dipping sauce which taste lilke the golden curry packet. Probably not, but it needed that differentiation. Okonomiyaki was a bit of a let down. Chilli jam prawns didn't go well and even though it's waffle type, there's no bite or crunch from the cabbage. Mi Goreng noodle is just a novelty imo. Coffee was alright, but the fruits in the juice seems not ripe enough. Overall food is fine, but expensive. I wasn't sure why the venue fee/surcharge is 15% when the holiday surcharge is only 10%.

name: Sandeep Kamath
snippet: Good coffee. Liked the light lunch. Awesome place to visit. Checkout the photos don‚Äôt remember the name üòú

name: Oliver Calman
snippet: Bit disappointed they got rid of the Mac and Cheese croissant. Overall the food and coffee were decent. The staff were very fussy, rearranging drinks on our table while we were eating, and removing a napkin I was in the middle of using. They even took a half finished drink off the table. Given the long lines outside I figured it was a not so subtle request to leave so they could get more food orders.

name: Ella Bassett
snippet: I love the cuckoo callay in Newtown so I had high expectations for the Surry hills venue. My partner and I wanted to order some breakfast and I really liked the look of the breakfast wrap on the ‚Äútakeaway only‚Äù menu but was told that I couldn‚Äôt order it to eat in. To be honest I‚Äôm not one to leave negative reviews and I understand it‚Äôs not the staffs fault that it is set up this way but it‚Äôs almost comical that food coming from the SAME kitchen cannot be eaten whilst sitting down? I truly would understand if it was takeaway only in the sense that the dine in food was too difficult to make to take away but the other way around just makes absolutely no sense and management should make some sort of change with that or Atleast give the staff a justification to tell customers when asked about the rule. I‚Äôm disappointed.

name: Monica Tsui
snippet: Food was tasty but portions were very small considering the price.Though service was good!

name: George Karystianis
snippet: Cosy place, great music, fantastic coffee! The stuff though are hit and miss. They either like you and they show it or can't be asked serving you. Furthermore, their menu is not for someone who wants something simple to eat as it tends towards hipster choices.

name: Paul Napier
snippet: This is a quirky and interesting venue with a lot of unique ideas. However, the food is a little of the pretentious side and somewhat overpriced. The service is good and the staff extremely friendly, but if you are a plain food fanatic (no sauces and no over the top ingredients) then this is really not the best place for you. However, if you are a gourmand and experimentalist, then it probably is. Sadly, I am the former :(

name: Emie Fernandez
snippet: Coffee and juice were good, but not impressed by the food. Eggs were overcooked. The menu is lacking sweet options for breakfast. On a brighter note, the staff was very nice and the ambiance is good.

name: penny cai
snippet: Suzie Q is located on Hutchison Street in Surry Hills. It is in a quiet spot and serves really good coffee. There are old records that aren't for sale and a DJ that comes in to play from time to time. Even though I love the coffee, the food is a little disappointing. I tried the Arepas was a little too dry and hard to eat as well as a touch bland. I shall be back to try out more dishes before I give my final verdict. But if you are in the area, go grab a coffee!

name: Old Man Jed
snippet: A bit too laid back with regard to "service" but food is okay and coffee is nice. Not too expensive, given the options.

name: Elliot Pahl
snippet: Very hit and miss, van be great or disappointing. Don't expect the specials to be available if you aren't there super early.

name: ana k
snippet: Nice place to have coffee.

name: Guilda Tabar
snippet: Extremely original

name: IKREEZY
snippet: A very cute brunch spot, tucked away from the busy Sydney roads. $$: ‚Äòrecord‚Äô style designed menus with affordable prices. Settings: amazing ambience inside and outside seating areas of the cafe. Staff was very delightful

name: Carrie Chi
snippet: Nice coffee and food here. A great little cafe with a cosy vibe. The coffee is unique that I never had before.

name: Bin Li
snippet: Outstanding house rose petal and buckwheat granola with coconut yoghurt stewed autumn fruits. The coffee was excellent with near perfect microfoam. But be sure to specify if you want table service or take away.

name: Abbie Love
snippet: A lovely local coffee shop and cafe with a range of good options to cater to all tastes. Vegan and vegetarian friendly with some epic options for both - the cauliflower was amazing. If you add extras a brunch can quickly become $35+ with coffee, which is on the higher side. Dog friendly outside and a good vibe inside.

name: Timothy Vandeputte
snippet: Great coffee but a bit expensive (espresso 3.8$). Nice seating area. Small selection of records.

name: Maria Tucker
snippet: Hipster little cafe. Although small has great food with a well thought out menu, service and vibe. The service is happy efficient and helpful. The music is eclectic and creates really fun vibe and as tea and coffe drinkers we were all pleased.

name: Vrunda
snippet: They had one of the best sandwiches on their takeaway menu but sadly now it‚Äôs no longer on it. Which makes me so sad! But otherwise this place is lovely. Good coffee and the staff is so friendly.

name: grace tham
snippet: Looking for a lazy Sunday lunch spot, we decided to try out this hidden gem of a cafe. The funky selection of vinyl record music that greeted us was rivaled only by the welcoming smiles and genuine warmth of the staff. The cafe has a relaxed and inviting vibe - the kind of place you could bring friends for lazy lunches or just yourself and a book for a quiet seat at the sunny windows. We had a hard time picking from the delectable menu. Eventually, we settled on the Asian inspired crispy fried eggs with crab which was delicious! The coffee and sticky chai, much like our meals, were full flavored and spot on. It's a shame we missed out on the baked sweets - will have to be back for them soon! Tip: the venue is also licensed so do enquire about functions and larger group bookings!

name: Dan Brennan
snippet: Coffee was good,. Got a hipster roll (bacon and egg roll - party included) was bit suspect getting of the premade roll on display but was surprising awesome - not sure if possible but imagine would be even better if made fresh rather than being reheated!

name: Kitty Cat
snippet: Stools where pretty uncomfy, food was great for something different, unique and delicious flavour palette, staff helpful, venue and playlist just lovely, coffee was ok but didn't finish regular latte.

name: Esther Brown
snippet: We loved this little laid-back cafe down one of the quieter blocks in Surry Hills. The obvious theme here is music. The menus are made from record sleeves and each item on the menu is musically themed. Despite the fun names, the menu here isn‚Äôt too incredibly unique from the other Surry Hills cafes ‚Äì but they take even the most simple dish to the next level with clever seasoning and fresh ingredients. I had the Eggs and Sausage in a Cadillac with Susan Mitchelson (Arepa with Melted Cheese, Choriza, Fried Egg & Salsa. I was a bit dissapointed to find out that they were out of Arepas (corn meal flat bread) and would replace it with white bread, but it actually was still delicious. Well-seasoned and super flavourful. McKay had the daily special ‚Äì smoked salmon with an omelette on toast. Again ‚Äì while it isn‚Äôt a unique dish that you couldn‚Äôt find elsewhere in Surry Hills ‚Äì the flavours were on point. There aren‚Äôt very many sweet options. No pancakes or french toast, but they did look to have a pretty delicious selection of pastries.

name: Robert Patterson-Hyde
snippet: Delicious,well executed menu. Friendly service. My current favourite brunch place.

name: E Y
snippet: No bad

name: Ivan Lim
snippet: Food and coffee were great. Place is quite small so there were not many seats

name: KV T
snippet: Always delivers everytime. Menu changes seasonally and always tasty.

name: Barbara Qin
snippet: Good coffee, haven't tried food there. Quite place.

name: Benjamin Bywater
snippet: Good food and coffee. Only let down was the service was a bit slow.

name: Mark Smith
snippet: Busy for breakfast. Take note of the specials. Good coffee

name: H J
snippet: Extremely bad service and worst coffee...shouldn't be a barista when there are no customer skills and know how to make a cup of coffee.

name: Alexander Duran
snippet: Rude Chinese lady

name: Robert Beecroft
snippet: Ordered a small latte which was barely 3cm filled up. I order small coffees in my 8oz cup which at least fill halfway at every other shop. Very disappointing

name: Vicki Palacios
snippet: Super pretentious. Went here this morning and was trying to politely ask for a a small coffee with a smaller shot... unfortunately I didn‚Äôt use the term ‚Äúweak‚Äù so the waitress (short bleached hair) saw fit to patronise me and then call out two passive aggressive comments as she walked across the cafe. It‚Äôs very chic at this cafe (hence the extra star) but not worth being made to feel like an idiot for making a simple request.

name: Nick Laz
snippet: Popular cafe for the area, staff friendly and helpful. Seating inside and some stools outside. Coffee is ok but not my favourite.

name: Sarah Wright
snippet: Coffee was alright but service was atrocious. Walked in and three servers were at the counter. None acknowledged me, so wasn‚Äôt sure whether it table service or not. Nonetheless, I took a seat thinking they‚Äôll come around. After 5 minutes or so they said I have to order at the counter first. There‚Äôs plenty of decent cafes around that area, won‚Äôt be back.

name: Anna Mullins
snippet: Ok coffee but it is served luke warm (at best). I asked for my coffee to be made hotter today and still it's luke warm. Not buying from here again.

name: Mark Vaughn
snippet: A bit over hyped, no internet according to the staff (came here on a recommendation from an article stating they had great internet)No cream and sugar station. Pretty pretentious vibe.

name: Wojtek Bereza
snippet: Closes early so watch out.

name: Kate Link
snippet: Great coffee and yummy patries, but I was a bit disappointed with the service. Some of the baristas were very warm and friendly. Others clearly spotted someone from out of town and sent me to the bar/resturant next door for a toilet when there are public toilets one level below the shop. Ask some of the regular patrons for wifi and toilet info.

name: Greg Dylewski
snippet: I've now had the coffee twice, both times barely warm and unimpressive taste. I think the pastries and staff are lovely though.

name: Alex H.
snippet: An example of a cafe trying to be hipster, but not doing it very well. Coffee was great although the staff member couldn‚Äôt tell me origin/bean type (I found the cards as photographed), kept calling me mate with an odd, almost demeaning nuance, and finally spilled my coffee when bringing it out; being bizarrely unapologetic about it when I tried to clean the cup (why am I doing that for them?). It‚Äôs kind of that snobby indifferent service that you expect from a hipster joint, however without the chops to back it up. Coconut croissant was bomb though. A very hesitant 4 stars.

name: Jeremie Sneddon
snippet: Coffee was nice, however a Piccolo should be served in an 100ml glass. Don't like the little cups you guys use. Pretty sure they are about 80ml.Service was friendly, nice staff. Good clean atmosphere.

name: Rhys Travels
snippet: Lovely coffee and service. The outdoor area was nice in an autumn morning.

name: De De
snippet: Nice atmosphere and good service. $5.50 for a flat white is extreme. The coffee was nice but a little weak. Good experience but would not go back at those prices.

name: francine a
snippet: This coffee feels strong and mean. They have different blends but I taste cherry in most cups from here. This place also sells coffee merch such artisan mugs and cafeti√®res. The place itself is nice with a cool concrete interior and lots of dogs walking past. I wish the serving sizes were larger but a Starbucks grande of this brew would give me a heart attack; so maybe not.

name: Peter Chia
snippet: Great coffee, definitely with come back again next time. üëçüèºüëçüèº

name: Prasant Dewan
snippet: This joint definitely took coffee making to a holistic level! Feels calm, even the caffeine there! Minimalist but mind it quality coffee and service! Take away - Yes Toilet - Went for coffee not the toilet, don't know Cost - Normal

name: Tulin Sevgin
snippet: Great coffee, was a bit disappointed with the service the first time I went there. Second time was better however consumed a bit too much coffee and there is no bathroom here so keep that in mind.

name: Tom Woolnough
snippet: Great coffee, lovely airy space.No power outlets; if you‚Äôre planning on working for an extended period, this is not the place unfortunately.

name: Paul Vermeer
snippet: Excellent coffee and cake. I bought some of their roast coffee to take home

name: Yoyo
snippet: Nice coffee and Matcha latte

name: D VR
snippet: Minimal interior with extravagant good coffee. Yet not the best service experience.

name: Matt Martin
snippet: Excellent. Lovely coffee and friendly efficient staff.

name: Gerrod Schirtzinger
snippet: Good coffee, but wifi was rather slow and there are no toilets.

name: Timothy Olliver
snippet: Good coffee.

name: Matthew Moore
snippet: Nice place

name: Shiko Maruyama
snippet: (Translated by Google) A cozy cafe with delicious coffee. Because it is a large shared table, it is not suitable for work and reading alone.
