snippet: (Translated by Google) Donuts & coffee are great üëç(Original)ÎèÑÎÑõ&Ïª§Ìîº Íµ≥Íµ≥üëç

name: Derek Jenkins
snippet: 45mins (no exaggeration) for coffee and *diabolically overcooked* poached eggs on toast. This morning (Sunday) they had just one person trying to run front of house while two of the slowest cooks known to mankind were in the kitchen. To top it off, phone based NFC payment not possible because of the sh*tty iPad-based POS system they use. An altogether underwhelming return visit to this place. They've lost my business. Fourth visit has been my last. Sorry guys, not good enough.

name: Trav Augustus
snippet: Exceptionally bad coffee. I have been here twice now and both times have had horrendous coffee. A good rule of thumb is, if your staff are unable to texture a certain milk appropriately, then don't offer that type of milk. Surely a business of this caliber should be getting the basics right. Consider using 8oz cups instead of 6oz cups and ensuring the baristas are adequately trained to handle the coffee making process. Outside of that, the pictures speak for themselves.

name: Natasha Huang
snippet: Exceptionally bad coffee. I ordered the flat white but give me the cappuccino... never drink anymore. A good rule of thumb is ensuring the baristas are adequately trained to handle the coffee making process.

name: Jul V
snippet: Nice place, however I wasn't happy with the food and service. I ordered egg benedict and the served my eggs with japanese style poach eggs (supper running), I told one of the waitress that the eggs are too running and the only option that she gave me was to give me a plate to put them aside. Also the man a the counter asked how was the food and we explain what happened and he just apologised. So, what it suppose to be a good experience for my Sunday breakfast end up in a bad food experience.

name: Bry H
snippet: Finally able to find a cafe that could screw up bacon. Overall very mediocre and under seasoned food which neither was placed in realms of japanese integrity or asian deliciousness. Coffee game weak albeit hipster outfits adorned by baristas. Service inefficient at non peak hour. Only high quality was prices. Expected from a heart following collective that did not have a dose of reality. However, good place for instagram, chill with the cool furniture and able to book tables if you have 4 pax min.

name: Tatiana Sheehan
snippet: Not sure what all this hype is about. My friend and I visited Meet Mica on 4/7. We have never been to this cafe before and were really looking forward to it. We were seated and given two menus. I didn't ave any time to browse around the cafe - we just came in and sat down straight away. I wanted to get mocha and croissant. In the menu it is stated: Croissants and cakes - please check with our staff for daily choices. So I ordered a small mocha first, and asked the guy which croissants they had for the day. And he said almond, chocolate and something else. I love chocolate croissants! And that's what I ordered. My mocha came first. I would say I didn't enjoy it much - yes, the unicorn was pretty, but I would prefer good taste over looks. I couldn't really tell that it was mocha because there was no chocolate in the taste. I buy mocha specifically because I prefer chocolate coffee. Otherwise I would have bough cappuccino. If you offer this coffee to anyone - without telling them it's mocha - they would never be able to guess it's actually mocha. And then my pastry came. Well. I ordered a chocolate croissant. What I got was not a croissant. It was a different pastry. Look, I come from the Europe part of the world. Western food and western pastries are important for me. 'A croissant is a buttery, flaky, viennoiserie pastry of Austrian origin, named for its historical crescent shape'. Crescent shape. That's a part of croissant. I was given a different type of pastry. You might say: Oh what's the issue, it's still a chocolate pastry! Well! If I go to a restaurant and ask them for hoki, but they bring me catfish saying - oh, it's still white fish, you can eat it! Does it sound right? No. Another issue - I cut this pastry in two halves and peeped inside. Nearly NO chocolate at all! AT ALL! Make sure your partners provide you with good pastry! When we were paying the bill, I noticed croissants and other pastries near the counter. I hope it's display only? Because you are not allowed to keep food in that area? Anyway, I was very upset with my visit to Meet Mica: absolutely couldn't understand why I paid more specifically for mocha when I wasn't even able to tell that it was actually mocha, and getting another type of pastry when I clearly ordered croissant... Well. I'm done with this place. :) I sent them an email after the visit - no reaction. No simple apology. Copied the text into Google reviews. Got a reply 25 minutes later. :) Saying that I am a constantly grumpy person so they are sorry for me. :) Well FYI all positive reviews are published in my blog - negative reviews are published there as well, however it's not in English so you won't be able to read it / understand it. Google reviews in my case are mostly for complaining out loud in English - and I am absolutely allowed to do that. A simple apology via email would have saved the situation - I don't need more. But your Google reviews reply ruined everything completely. :) Thanks

name: Yuliana Yuliana
snippet: We going to have a brunch today, the food look so good, it was taste so good as well when it hot, the food coming it's become cold already, and we have to wait almost 30 minutes for the food, I just see that wasn't that much table in the place but the service was really slow!!! and also the coffee as well , we ordered a mocha but we feel we not got a mocha, I fell it was really bad experience to eat at that place, Hope they can improve they service!!!!

name: Mo Yang
snippet: That is the worst experience in Sydney. We have waited for the brunch for more than 40 mins but the staff just say‚Äúwe also wait for u guys 20 mins‚Äù? I am so angry about this brunch store . I am sorry for our late, but this is not the reason that you let us wait for 40 mins.

name: K
snippet: Slow service - a perfect place if you have hours to waste When they tell you it's a 15-20min wait, what they actually meant was 150min to 200min. So realistically, it's more than an hour to get a table and another hour to get served.

name: Robert Beecroft
snippet: Went to the bathroom that leads out behind the shop, only to return and they had locked me out lol. I knocked on the back door quite hard for a few minutes, considering staff were only metres away from me I almost wonder how it wasn't possible to hear this. Luckily I saw the back entrance of the hairdresser next door and asked if I could come through their shop. Obviously I can laugh about this but it was highly embarrassing and very unprofessional of the cafe to not be aware of their own patrons they're taking care of.

name: Jennifer R
snippet: I had high hopes given the reviews but we were served a bland berry muffin and stale almond croissant. Sorry we won‚Äôt return.

name: Megan Bassman
snippet: Waited in line for 30mins with our name on a list, table became available but they wouldn't give it to us, waiting on other people who weren't there to show up. There was no hustle, no sense of urgency, we were there and ready to order before a show but wouldn't be accommodated.

name: Lachlan Wood
snippet: Worst service I have ever experienced, cannot speak about the food or coffee as it never came. I left after 30 mins of waiting. Don't waste your time at this cafe.

name: sanaz aval
snippet: I just went to get 2 takeaway coffee and a banana bread and came to $15 the coffe size was small I think a beat bigger then espresso cup so over price and because it was skim they charge extra 50 cent the banana bread $ 7 95 for take away and taste not even good and I been to lots of cafe I can tell this was the worst banana bread I ever had and over priced been to so much cafe and the most overpriced and worst banana bread so far

name: miek99
snippet: Waited over 40 mins for 2 orders and was about to leave.

name: afhiem Z
snippet: Terrible service. Worst

name: Dee
snippet: Wait is too long

name: SHUJIE CHENG
snippet: Terrible service

name: Phoebe L
snippet: Service was friendly and nice clean decor however the food is overrated and doesn‚Äôt deliver in taste to how it actually sounds written. The main purpose seems to be for Insta shots. Had the matcha lace French toast - the bread tasted stale, hard and chewy and the matcha sauce that exploded was quite tasteless, a dismal side serve of fruit salad too. The other fish we had was the A Bowl (shiitake mushroom, miso chicken, barley grains poached egg, corn & greens in broth) which was way too salty and unbalanced in their portions of the components with too much barley. Bad acoustics indoors with all hard furnishings could hardly hear each other talk. The only saving grace was their coffee but that‚Äôs cos they use the little marionette coffee which is one of my personal faves. Overhyped place, def won‚Äôt be back. much nicer places elsewhere.

name: yuanming xie
snippet: Disgusting mocha toast though look good. My friends and I ordered a bowl, tataki soumen(beef noodle), and lobster congee. Really bad experience. Coffee is nice though. Don't recommend the restroom.

name: Rachel Hill
snippet: I was expecting more Asian/Japanese fusion dishes but it was pretty much just your typical brunch menu save for around 5 signature options. We tried the lobster congee and crab croissant from the signature menu - the congee was okay, but not at all worth $32 (?!) and I couldn't taste or see any crab in the croissant at all. The coffee was a little flavourless, came out warm rather than hot and I also thought the cup it came in was really small. Service-wise, the waitress was really nice, but it took ages for us to be seated when we were at the front of the line and there were empty tables, and it took a while for the coffee to come out. Overall, everything was overpriced and I wouldn't come back again.

name: Martin Varga
snippet: Beautiful minimalist decor, plenty of sunlight and good coffee but bad food and seating layout. Ordered "A bowl" which was rated as delicious in another review, and it looked beautiful, but it was really bad. The broth was mediocre, the chicken burned. The rest of the ingredients and the bowl overall were tasteless. Rest of the menu did not seem attractive to me as I wanted a savoury dish, but the matcha french toast might be nice. Their pastry seemed old. My muffin was reheated and had frozen core, croissant must have been good when fresh (the filling was nice), but it was chewy. Coffee was good, served with a little matcha cookie. Seating was somewhat inconvenient - a few large tables, but not enough seating for couples and singles.

name: Mavis HU
snippet: The photo with little pot was my first time at Sep to eat and others are shot today. The size is much smaller than before and the bread is suck, no chewy at all.

name: ÂæêÁ•éÊ¥Å
snippet: One waiter over there are stubborn and offers bad service. It seems he thinks this restaurant is too popular and he can treat the customers badly? I mean a male one :)Ôºå food seems all good but long wait, I'm so pissed off now and have to give 2 stars

name: melzy phan
snippet: Drinks were subpar, with the iced teas tasting mostly like water and hojicha latte on ice having large powder clumps. Service was a little on slower side but it was a little busy 2 stars since food and service was okay but probably would not return.

name: Alex Macintosh
snippet: Highly overrated cafe. The dishes are aesthetically pleasing and certainly Instagram-worthy but severely lacking in taste. We had the green tea soba with seared duck and the crab croissant. Both dishes were underwhelming and disappointing, considering the price we paid. There was barely any duck or crab. The croissant was stale and seemed like it had been sitting there for a while. The iced chocolate was standard - good but not spectacular. The only positive was the friendly service by the waiters. Food also took a while to come out. Considering the location, there are much better brunch places around.

name: Linen Su
snippet: Good service.But the place is too crowded.Food was not as good as expected from their reviews.Price is a bit high for some plates.

name: Amy Truong
snippet: Great presentation however that's really the only positive. Ordered the lobster congee and the A bowl. The congee hadn't been reheated properly and came out cold. Both dishes lacked flavour and overall service was fairly slow. Wasn't inedible but not worth a second visit.

name: Sien Liu
snippet: Overrated place. Food was mediocre. The matcha toast is too strong on tea flavour. Its the matcha flavour acceptable by Japanese people. Service is also slow. Waited 30 mins for our food to be served. Definitely will not recommend.

name: Rein Fa
snippet: They got decent coffee and teas. Mediocre for the foods, nothing special really. We order the macha lava toast (not sure if thats the exact name) and the bento btw. Anyway the service is very slow and odd. The waitstaff that serve us somehow got confused when we simply correct her that we want two hojicha teas. When she brought one tea set, we asked her again to make sure she understands that we order two set, but she suddenly come to conclusions that we want one extra cup, which doesn't make sense. We also asked for extra napkins and water, which at the end it never come.

name: Shana Ross Libiran
snippet: Coffee is good but ver slow service! I only ordered regular croissant and my friend ordered matcha lava toast but took them 30 mins! Waste of time!

name: Jazer Ocfemia
snippet: Chances of meeting Mica? Zero. After waiting at the door for an unreasonable amount of time, we still hadn't even been greeted even when I had looked at staff in the eye. They seemed to dart away and seemed to be scared to even interact with or give a smile to the queue outside. Not good when you're positioned in a competitive caf√© area. We walked over to Cook & Archie's and even though there was also a queue, were greeted straight away, put on a list and handed menus to read. Even a small thing like that is reasonable standard service.

name: N Daniel
snippet: Matcha lava French Toast looks great but taste so-so.Tonkatsu Bento, any Japanese restaurant can do better and with half price.

name: Rose Kean
snippet: My food took ages and came out cold and had a hair in it and they forgot my coffee so not great.

name: G Kim
snippet: Could improve a lot on glasses and dishes (cleanliness-wise)

name: Veronica Tay
snippet: Firstly, my intention is to state the facts and give constructive criticism. Our first visit to this cafe was mostly positive. We ordered the omurice, karaage sanga, ice matcha latte and matcha milkshake. We had a good experience and enjoyed the food overall, particularly we appreciated the flexibility to have kimchi on the side as my husband can‚Äôt have it. My omurice was decent but I didn‚Äôt finish it because the onion was too overpowering. The egg was soft and fluffy, I loved that. The sauce was paired well and helped to balance the flavours on the dish overall. The drinks were excellent, strong and punchy matcha flavours if you enjoy that. We enjoyed it so much that we decided to go for a second visit the following weekend and brought a friend along too. However, this time for whatever reason the waitress denied the exact same order, checked with the kitchen and came back with just as strong an opinion that that simply cannot fulfil our order of having kimchi on the side. We explained that he couldn‚Äôt eat it with the kimchi inside but they just said no if you want to eat it, you must have the kimchi. So we opted not to order anything savoury and just go for lunch elsewhere. I tried the matcha mille feuille but I must say.. it looks way better than it tastes. The mille feuille was dry and didn‚Äôt have much taste, the matcha creme was grainy and did not add moisture to balance the dish. Needless to say, we will not be coming back, service is appalling and food is just average. Go for it if you like instagramable food but lower your expectations for everything else.

name: Tina
snippet: Note to self: don‚Äôt come here again. First time was bad. Second time just confirmed it actually is bad. Food is pretty but tastes very mediocre.

name: Anthea Jacklin
snippet: Be warned ordering the French toast! it is NOT French toast. I had an very annoying and upsetting experience when I ordered the French toast and received literally just a piece of toast (no egg at all) with banana and peanut butter. put aside the fact that it was very overpriced at $19, when I made a comment to the service staff I was told that 'the chef is trying something different and is making new and interesting things'. Well this is just wrong, sure.... say it's a deconstructed French toast, or French toast with a twist... but don't just call your meal French toast and then serve toast. Not cool man. Not cool.

name: Imogen Gray
snippet: Although this cafe makes excellent coffee, me and two friends ate the brekky burger, none of us were able to finish it as it was actually repulsive. The bacon option was thicker than a finger and doused in wasabi, it was effectively spam. The salmon could be likened to cat food and was similarly disgusting. Avoid eating here.

name: Lana Havy Dinh
snippet: Food wasn‚Äôt fresh and smelled weird , I‚Äôm not sure if they even use gloves to make the sandwiches. It was super hot in the cafe and the employees seemed like they need some water and a new dry shirt . All in all I don‚Äôt get the hype no sandwich or whatever is worth sitting in a cafe without air conditioning and bad vibes .

name: Amaris Cookie
snippet: send in a customer feedback abt their food thru insta but they ignored it.. i guess if you want better customer service, better quality, tasty and better presentation cafe food go to their sister cafe instead.. i think that‚Äôs where the owner chef is at cuz the food there is great but kentaro pales in comparison.. what a pity.. wasted so much money at kentaro, my friend didn‚Äôt even finish her soba salad

name: ashlee yao
snippet: Never ever come back!!!Not nicely to the family with kids. Very rude!!!!

name: Chihiro Suto
snippet: 0 stars. I won‚Äôt never come here even I haven‚Äôt tried their foods. Their staff are too bad personality. They called me ‚ÄúBusu‚Äù which means ‚Äúugly ‚Äúin Japanese. Not even once , they called me many times.

name: Marcus Pham
snippet: The bad owner and braindead manager when someone ask for sauce, they are not allowed to separate sauce and the course. I came there several times but i can recognise why no one wants to come to try this shop. So dirty and old even though they try to make it like retro

name: Kayla Wu
snippet: Don‚Äôt know about the food, service was terrible. Been there 3 times, the staff there were never attentive, asked for a seat and got told to wait 20mins. 20mins after 20mins, no one was looking after the waiting customer

name: Shannon Brunsdon
snippet: Customer service appalling, leaving customers standing waiting for up to 30 minutes with empty tables. Basic hospitality. Very disappointing.
