name: Sangeun Park
snippet: i went there with my friends. dont understand the hype.

name: Kumiko Hira
snippet: Never going there again.

name: Marx Huang
snippet: Waited 50 min, the omurice was lukewarm, not hot and the taste was nothing special. Matcha Croffle was extremely hard and not fluffy, seemed a bit stale and not worth the price for sure. Good customer service, friendly guy. Coffee was ok too. Overall, underwhelming.

name: vanessa wong
snippet: Just a bad day? Went there last month noticed some menu changes. Most disappointed with the squid ink paella. The rice was hard and not well cooked. Bread used for the pork katsu was noticeably not fresh. Only the coffee was OK.

name: Maggie Chen
snippet: This is my first time writing review. I had a really unhappy experience in here. It's a rainning day, waiting outside for long time. The service mistake the waiting list order TWICE. And foods need to wait another 15-20 mins. We are sitting at an unstable and oblique table with rainning on shoulder. The fluffy omurice was a must try, but the katsu sandwich was just an average. P.S If you want to come on the weekends at noon, I won't recommend you here.

name: Faith Moana
snippet: The service is okay, but food is just ordinary. The soft shell crab burger - buns are too sweet. Omurice - mushroom sauce too salty. They should have a better consistency in flavour. The price is Sydney‚Äôs average. Once is enough, you can try it.

name: Allyson Neo
snippet: We love Japanese food and was eager to check out this place. Unfortunately it was yet another letdown.. Portion sizes were seriously small for the price you pay. We weren't even full after having lunch there. Also go easy on the green tea powder for the matcha iced tea. It was really hard to stomach.

name: Michelle Lam
snippet: The Katsu sandwich did taste good but I felt it was impractically really big to eat, and fell everywhere and all over my fingers. Some staff members were friendly but there was a female who served me and I asked for some ice as it was a very hot day (one of the hottest days in Sydney). She gave me an uncomfortable vibe and came back with one cube of ice. I eventually asked for more as it was a hot day but felt uncomfortable asking. When starbucks hands out like half a cup of ice to everyone in a drink - i just think ice is not much to ask. Besides I did order an iced coffee too.

name: Andrew H
snippet: We visited during the recent long weekend. Three people, three dishes, two serves of chips. The Kentaro Style Omurice was delicious and definitely worth a try. The Aonori Chips were a nice compliment and the portion size was good compared to the lotus root chips which we also ordered, these were however soft and not crunchy, you can tell they weren't freshly fried. My partner insisted on trying the signature pork sandwich, and wow looks can be deceiving. The pork katsu was very thick and just generally difficult to chew, the sandwich bread was cold. However the most disappointing was the Beef Motsu Nabe - the flavour was interesting to try, but not something you would re-order. The tripe in the dish was completely inedible, it was chewy and very very tough, perhaps the chef intended the tripe not to be eaten but only for flavor? This cafe came highly recommended after visiting their sister cafe in Redfern, sadly we will never return.

name: Kayla Medica
snippet: We came as a group of 5 at 1:30pm. After ordering and not being told of any sold out items, the waitress came back to say some menu items were no longer available, so we changed our order... Then she came back again to tell us the items we had just selected were also sold out. Then after correcting our order again, the food came out first with only 3 out of 5 dishes with a bit of a wait before the fourth came out and a good 45 minutes wait until the fifth dish came out. The first four were all finished eating before the 5th came out and in that time we didn't get any updates from the wait staff. We had to finally flag someone down just to be told "they're preparing it now". The food is ok, but I guess we only got to pick from the less popular dishes. Was really disappointed in the customer service and would not come back.

name: Eugene Liu
snippet: Tiny portions, not very tasty, tastes like soba noodles from an instant packet, chicken was stringy and dry. Was hoping for a good meal and ended up with a below average expensive one. I'm still hungry after spending $30

name: Reinaldo Ranti
snippet: Ergh...... Average, the Soba Salad was ok üëåüèª, though the Katsu Sandwich is well below average. The meat was dry, not enough fatty bits, only sauce was mustard.... not Japanese mustard, I‚Äôd assume mustard off the Colesr shelves. Really need to learn from Sando Bar, learn from a real Japanese.

name: Elizabeth Chau
snippet: Coffee is great unfortunately not the whole menu is temping to me. Been here several times staff is welcoming, but the mushroom on toast is such a buzz killer and I‚Äôm probably not coming back again.

name: Vincent Lam
snippet: Very average service and food here.

name: Vivian Lai
snippet: The place is cute and all the staff were super friendly and helpful. The Omurice was good but a bit too cheesy so I couldn‚Äôt finish it. Most of the food was good. The desserts were more disappointing. The mille-feuille was super tiny and the waffles were soggy. I would give it 3.5 stars.

name: Megan Chiew
snippet: Lovely cafe with eggcellant service, we enjoyed the omurice and crab omelette. The portion of crab omelette is slightly small but still tasty. Unfortunately not a fan of the katsu sandwich as the meat was too thick. Average coffee, matcha latte was great!

name: Kassi Merkouris
snippet: Food was tasty and coffee very nice; accidentally was overcharged and staff were helpful to sort it out and give a refund. Waitress however made us feel rushed after taking a coffee mug which was still half full and a plate off the table while still chewing the last bite.

name: R E
snippet: I had omelette rice, matcha millefeuille and almond flat white. I guess my expectation was a little bit high, the food was okay, however, unfortunately the dessert wasn‚Äôt my taste. It looked really pretty and photogenic, you know, but the matcha cream was too thick, something like thick butter cream...not smooth nor creamy...also the black sauce was quite bitter and tasted funny to me. a little bit disappointed as it was the most expensive dessert they had in the list. ( by the way my friend had the same dessert and she agreed with me about the matcha cream...) stars go to the nice atmosphere and almond flat white, I enjoyed.

name: Amy Chan
snippet: I came here last Sunday after looking at the amazing pictures on Zomato. I provided my phone number and name and the staff put us in the digital waiting list and told me I would get a notification once the table was ready. I got a text message with a link straight away to check the updates. After 40 minutes of waiting in the car nearby because it was raining, I clicked onto the link again and it said we were no longer on the waiting list !!!! I ran back to the cafe to see both the staffs were not holding onto the iPad and just seating the walk ins‚Ä¶. Yes I am certain they were walk ins. They walked up and asked if there was a table and was told to check in and sit down. When I came back they had a table for us, but we wouldn‚Äôt have known because there was no notification ?? The food was okay. I feel that after that experience before the meal, my partner and I were already in a pretty bad mood to enjoy the food impartially. All I want to say is, please review whether the digital waiting list system is fully working before adopting it or speak to the service provider about these issues‚Ä¶ because it‚Äôs not fair.

name: Viki O‚ÄôHagan
snippet: Went for sunday brunch. Really enjoyed my matcha bircher muesli, was like nothing I‚Äôd ever had before and was delicious. My boyfriend ordered the miso mushrooms with poached eggs. The eggs were under cooked slightly and you pay $5 for extra tomato which is just a raw tomato- expected it cooked at $5?! When we told the waiter that the egg was under cooked she just shrugged and walked off. We then told another waiter who was very attentive and got it swapped for another egg & new toast. They also took the tomato off the bill which was good of them. I recon it‚Äôs slightly over rated but worth checking out for the unusual brunch items.

name: Mr R
snippet: So so. Nothing to write home about. Been to cafes so much better. Can only give them 3 stars.

name: Tricia Fallows
snippet: A bit overrated. The food was good but not mind blowing.

name: Y M
snippet: A good breakfast / coffee spot

name: Anthony Anthony
snippet: Ok coffee

name: Z. Deutch
snippet: Overpriced, average tasting food.

name: Chai Lim
snippet: Very disappointed in the coffee. It took over 15 minutes to get a takeaway long black. There was only 1 coffee order in front of mine. $4 for a small coffee is overpriced. The coffee itself was unremarkable. A waste of Marvell St coffee :(

name: Matthew Sloane
snippet: Heavy on the shift, hold the F!!! Food was awful.

name: siren Rose
snippet: I cannot agree with those positive feedback about the food, find the flavour quite odd.

name: Samuel Beasley
snippet: Don‚Äôt go with more than 2 people or you‚Äôll be waiting over an hour.

name: Cassandra T
snippet: Food was nothing special. Ordered the vegan club sandwich and they toasted the lettuce. Thai faux beef salad was on the soggy side, average at best. Coffee was good and the carrot cake was delicious. Best thing was the friendly service and everyone saying bye when we left.

name: Atanas Chernev
snippet: Although tasty, I can‚Äôt justify paying $16 for a mushroom toastie. Since when is cheese, bread and vegetable so expensive? Other meat toasties in the city (Dutch Smuggler) are $9-10. For $17 you get a Pepito - huge Portuguese steak sandwich in a baguette from Encasa. Sorry, but your pricing is totally out of the money.

name: Lilly Logan
snippet: After spending $42 on a two person "meal", we wait for 25 minutes having ordered the avo toast ($17), and ham toastie ($10), while sipping on our small smoothie and latte. Generally when you pay $17 for avocado toast, you get two large slices of nice (not extremely tough to chew through) sourdough, and quite a bit of avocado. This one small, actually laughable, piece of sourdough has a spread of avocado and then is mountain'd with a tasteless combination to hide the fact that you got less avocado than Subway provides on a six inch sub. The ham toastie, the cheaper and larger of the two "meals" tastes like a discount version of something you could pay less for at Lord of the Fries, but with an excessive amount of what tastes like mayonnaise but they call cashew cream cheese. The banana smoothie was the only nice thing, if a little small in size. The iced latte was incredibly bitter, like I now am, after spending too much money here.

name: Tanya Quach
snippet: Had the Reuben and cheese toasting here. The Sangas were abit of a disappointment - I was hoping they would have a little more flavour. The cheese toasting wasn't melty and the Reuben was a little dry. Overall, staff were friendly, ambience was nice but food wasn't worth the cost. There are better vegan options out there.

name: Ankur Passi
snippet: The service was really friendly and the food and coffee were also good. However $18 for the meatball sub was expensive comparative to other places around. It was more of a six inch sub with 4 meatballs. Nothing on the side as well. I liked my visit but had to spend $16 more for another take away sandwich. Overall it was a good experience in this nice cute cafe.

name: Parker
snippet: I have been wanting to try shift eatery for ages. Their menu offers many exciting options for vegetarians/vegans, however the execution was lazy, at least for the bagel sandwiches we ordered. The bagels themselves were perfect, but I think that‚Äôs because they use Brooklyn Boy Bagels (the best around Sydney). The filling was not as impressive. We got both options (the lox and bacon egg) and weren‚Äôt happy with either. The lox just tasted like a tomato bagel. I‚Äôm shocked by how little they did to achieve any sort of similar consistency. It didn‚Äôt taste bad, but they should just market it as a bagel with tomato. The bacon egg was better, but the egg tasted like scrambled tofu. I think my biggest issue was the marketing of the items to mimic meat dishes, yet tasting nothing like it. Obviously, we eat here to avoid eating meat, but that doesn‚Äôt mean you can sell a bagel as ‚Äúvegan lox‚Äù and have it be indistinguishable from tomato. Just advertise a tofu bagel and tomato bagel if that‚Äôs what you‚Äôre giving us. I‚Äôm so sad to be let this down. Maybe I‚Äôve overhyped it in my head for too long. I think I‚Äôll come back and try one of the sandwiches just to make sure I‚Äôm not missing anything.

name: Kirsty S (Kirst)
snippet: Accidentally found this place. Being lovers of meat we weren't thrilled to hear it was all vegan, but, we decided to stay as we were hungry. The good was very nice I must say! The Chai latte and coffee tasted feral and we couldn't finish it but we drink cows milk. So yes to the food although they seem to use fake meat. Cakes are super yum! Drinks, only if you like different milk like soy and nut milk....

name: Camilla Lucko
snippet: Vegan Cafe, staff seemed too casual.

name: Amy Elizabeth Nelson-Blain
snippet: Lots of great vegan options, tasty food and friendly staff. They do tend to have a lot of processed vegan foods though so it's not what I would consider super healthy but it's very tasty if you have a craving for their style of food! My only complaint is that it's very popular and the space is much too small to accommodate how many people seem to want to visit so expect to wait for a table. It's a shame it's not a bigger space but they may not have realised how popular it would be for the vegan community in Sydney! üòâ

name: Danni
snippet: The service wasnt very good. I had my name on the list for a table only to find out 20 minutes later that it had been crossed off and our table had been given away. When I brought this up we were told to "sit wherever you like", even though there wasn't capacity for our group of 3. When we were finally seated, the food came quickly and was quite tasty (though my friends toasted sandwich was undercooked). I'd probably revisit but would avoid busy times.

name: S. C
snippet: Service was good, friendly staff and great coffee. But I don‚Äôt think the pancake was tasty, maybe I‚Äôm not getting used to vegetarian meals. The pancake was too sweet and a little bit oily. I‚Äôll be back for coffee.

name: Nicole
snippet: The idea is nice, but if you like real milk and cheese, you should not eat there or drink the coffee!

name: Mae Lu
snippet: Ordered a hot chocolate and it‚Äôs cold...crying now. Food is good

name: mm ss
snippet: Decent vegan, too much imitation though.

name: Courtenay Turner
snippet: Not super tasty.

name: munkymandee
snippet: Very nice cafe with a chill playlist. Vegan food; i had the beetroot latte and ‚Äúsalmon‚Äù bagel. Was worried I wouldn‚Äôt feel full since it was tomatoes replacing the salmon but the serving size was really good! Loved the toasted crunch on the bagel and the cream cheese. All my friends really enjoyed their toasties as well. The smoothies look so good.

name: erinxeats
snippet: this is a really solid choice for vegans and the cashew cream cheese is one of the best i've had. i do wish they were a lil more generous with filling here as bagel takes up most of this cross-section i also was hoping it to be served in their iconic reusable milk cartons but this just came in a paper bag üòÖ i also got the 'my shroom toastie' üçÑ loaded with roasted mushrooms, basil pesto, cheddar, creamy herb sauce & toasted on some sweet sweet sourdough üçû delish! check out my food instagram @erinxeats for more!

name: Giulia
snippet: Very cute little vegan cafe with nice staff.I got the salmon bagel and it was delicious. My only suggestion would be the option to add more veggies on the side. That would be great!

name: freyafreyja
snippet: Lemon meringue tart was definitely a highlight!! It was lemony without being too sweet. Great with their good coffee. Bacon and egg bagel was delicious üòã we liked it better than the vegan reuben, but it is still great. Overall, they were yummy and we'd come back for more! Plus they are all vegan! Yaaayy!

name: Â∞èËçâ
snippet: Reasonable interior in a very close to Central Station location. As an Allium Free Vegan (Onion, Garlic, Leek, Shallot free) I have tried Smoked Tofu Sandwich Toasties, Big Bad Bowl after replace bean with Tofu and Carrot Cake. Tofu Sandwich Toasties is quite tasty. Toast sourdough bread was cooked to the right tender and to the right crusty brown. The Sauce was quite tasty, overall quality is fine. Big Bad Bowl was not recommended. One ingredient was the sauerkraut the shredded cabbage came with an unacceptable smell. While brown rice with quinoa, baked sweet potato and tofu are served warm and green salad are served in reasonable temperature, cherry tomatoes are served chill, this one does not comply with the overall temperature of the bowl. Sweet potato was baked with too strong herbal smell that it nearly lost the original nature of the sweet potato. Carrot cake was too sweet. I don‚Äôt think it fit Vegan‚Äôs taste of the sweetness.

name: Simon Guerin
snippet: Great cafe tucked away off the main roads of Surrey Hills. Excellent range of coffee options to choose from (Macadamia milk a welcome choice). Breakfast and lunch well covered. The shroom toasted sandwich is highly recommended! The Pad Thai was similarly delicious. Seating is limited so get in early if you want to eat in.

name: Craig Allen
snippet: The food and and service are really good, considering the location, it is difficult to get a place to sit that is great. The tables on the street are good to "eat and run", however if you want to have a mellow breakfast then give the place a miss, if you're happy sitting literally in the street, then the food is well worth it. The staff are friendly and the food is prompt, so all in all very good, just the location knocks of a perfect score sadly.

name: Dulan
snippet: Unfortunately I was disappointed by the shift Eatery has I had quite high expectations given what I have heard and it's rating. The food was good but was by no means the best vegan food that I have had. The menu is quite Limited , mostly to simple brunch items and a variety of sandwiches. We tried the pulled pork sandwich and the chicken schnitzel sandwich. The pulled pork uses jackfruit which we both felt was a poor substitute and quite an overpowering flavour. I would recommend the chicken sandwich though, which had similar texture to chicken. Despite the good substitute chicken, once again we were underwhelmed by the flavours. As compared to other brunch places in Sydney the food simply did not impress us. That said, it's great to have more vegan restaurants in Sydney and we paid $50 for 2 meals and 2 drinks. Note that the portion sizes for the sandwiches are fairly big

name: ÍπÄÏãúÏò®
snippet: I had the Cappuccino with almond milk and My Shroom Toastie. The vibe of the cafe is so nice, the staff were attentive! One downside is that I found that the seasoning of the toastie a bit too much, only as I don‚Äôt season a lot of my foods when eating. However, I really enjoyed the food and the great coffee!!!

name: J K
snippet: Yum but $18 for a sandwich ü•™üò¢

name: Bron Gordon
snippet: Great little vegan cafe with an awesome variety of options and quick, friendly service üíö

name: Y M
snippet: Food were good but nothing that blew my mind I suppose. It‚Äôs a nice little cozy cafe though

name: Triana MG
snippet: Didn't expect fake plants at a vegan restaurant...a part from that...good taste in what I tried... intrigued about those vegan eggs!

name: Christopher Brame
snippet: I can see why the Vegan Bacon and Egg Bagel sells out on the reg. Has to be one of the most satisfying goes at a vegan alternative I've ever eaten. Apsolutely awesome. The Reuben is also pretty decent!!

name: Emily Sarasa
snippet: Really great service but I thought the food was lacking some flavor. The bagel with lox was incredible, but the vegan egg was odd to me and the mango lassi was bland. We also had a tea cake, which was pretty dry. I‚Äôm not sure if we just ordered the wrong items. I would still go back and give it another try.

name: Ardently Verdant
snippet: Cruelty Free Food always tastes good & so wonderful to see more & more vegan eateries popping up all over Sydney! Overall positive experience at Shift Eatery. It‚Äôs a cool deli style eatery however quite small & mostly outdoor tables. That being said we were able to get seated on arrival. Staff were friendly & food arrived quickly after ordering via the me&u tap/order/pay system at the table. I had the Say Cheeeeese Toastie which was tasty af, made with the Bread & Butter Project sourdough.

name: Katie M
snippet: Best thing is the Nutie donuts!! Those things are super delicious!! Shift Eatery offers mainly sandwiches and they're pretty good, but nothing special. Everything is vegan which I love, but there's a heavy reliance on fake meat, which is a bit "meh" for me. Great coffees though!

name: Patrick Samuels
snippet: Join the club. Literally join the effin club The place make some awesome sandos, salads and coffee. I recommend the join the club, and I really do love this place, I use to go weekly however sadly late last year they had a price increase and it just pushed it for me to the point of being unaffordable. The vegan tax was really felt, and it‚Äôs understandable but what can you do. If you can afford it, it really is worth it, some really delicious food, sweets, coffee and drinks!

name: Yousef Dablin
snippet: This vegan place will literally shift your view of vegan food. Variety of food and desserts should please you. ü§§ü§§

name: Claire Y.
snippet: Decided to try this cafe before going in for an appointment about a month or two ago. Staff were friendly although quickly became one of my worst experiences in a cafe. I was served my drink and was waiting for my quiche. When I felt it was getting delayed, I told the waitress to instead make it a take away (as I was now running late). When the server brings it over, he accidentally knocks my coffee and spills it all over the table, me and the floor. He says sorry and brings over a handful of tissues. Lucky the drink wasn't hot otherwise i would've burnt myself. I hurriedly dry myself as I was now late for my appointment but no one offers to help clean up nor replace the drink! I didn't have time to ask and wait again so I was rushing to leave but as I was leaving, the lady i reminded of the quiche comes running out and yelling have I paid have I paid lol. What an experience is all I can say. Food and drink was average.

name: Kieran Richards
snippet: Terrible service, waited 20 minutes to be served, and only got served because I went to the counter to order and got told to sit back down. After ordering and waiting 30 minutes I checked on the order only to find out it hasn't even been started yet, despite other groups arrive after us that has been able to be served and eaten and left. With that we cancelled our food and, instead of apologising, they told us that this is standard to wait this long, and when we pointed out that other had been served much quicker they instead blamed us for not getting up and ordering (despite doing this and being told to sit down). Still then got charged for an average cup of tea and coffee without them once apologising. Just an all round rude and terrible experience.

name: Elliott Bledsoe
snippet: This place is all gimmick! Serving water out of reused Cooper's tallies into rusty camping mugs (I am not kidding, rusty cups!). This isn't a Frankie magazine photo shoot! Plus quips after practically every menu item is so obnoxious. And while we are on the menu, it sucks. The food was good, but you basically have four options. And the bill racks up with each addition. Plus they do not have EFTPOS.

name: siren Rose
snippet: Revolting absolutely revolting. Horrible taste. terrible customer service. Food quality is also below the average standard. Ridiculous price for the food and service they provide. Totally overpriced and ripped off. Never come back.

name: Frankly Morrissey
snippet: Coffee was burnt. When I bought this to their attention, the barrista reluctantly made another ‚Äî which was cold.Cafe was not clean either.Would not return.

name: Alexandra Taylor
snippet: We got asked to move tables, food was ok but we felt really cramped and the waitress forgot our order. Not a very relaxing environment.

name: Anna I
snippet: Waited over 40 minutes for food while everyone around us was being served. Definitely won‚Äôt be back.

name: Amir Jangodaz
snippet: Their chocolate brownie was solid as a rock!

name: Al Soepardi
snippet: Rates a 2.5/5. No floor staff here. The cashier n counter peeps double up to mind the tables. As they focus on takeaway customers, dine in folks get neglected. We were here on a quiet weekday for brekky and some of the items were not available. Like the bolognese eggs for eg. We ended up getting smoked salmon benny 2.5/5 n scrambled eggs on toast 2.75/5 (yawn*). Ordered a double macc but it looked single to me. It looks like they have changed hands so..

name: Anya Nguyen
snippet: I think i visited the cafe on their bad day. Did my research, saw that it‚Äôs among those top rated cafes in Sydney CBD (I already been to few others prior); I was quite excited to check out the cafe after reading so many good reviews... But my experience was quite disappointing. ‚Ä¢ Service: staffs were impolite apart from the first guy greeted me when i walked in. ‚Ä¢ Coffee was good but not great compare to other cafes i have been to during my visit in Sydney. ‚Ä¢ Food: i ordered eggs bene, decent portion but the eggs were over cooked

name: Dave Gordon
snippet: I have been really disappointed with my coffee on a few occasions, my cup is constantly 3/4 full, and a few times it looks like flat white volcanic eruption. The staff are very friendly, especially the personal greeting from the owner

name: Walter Spivak
snippet: Average coffee, poor food presentation, overcooked poached eggs. Lastly, eggs came with a side serve of egg shell... very poor form. Banana bread was nice though.

name: Rem Low
snippet: The rating is pretty misleading. Certainly not worthy for the prices charged (equivalent to hotel prices, should be $$$$) for a simple meal.

name: Suresh Kerai
snippet: This once great cafe has slowly lost the plot. Very disappointing.

name: Yuan Yao
snippet: It was okay. Wouldn‚Äôt mind going there again if a friend suggested it, but could not recommend it to others. Quite ordinary. I did ask for ham inside the omelette, it was not. Though I assured the waiter it was okay - but I‚Äôd still prefer to have things done correctly. Coffee was surprisingly good - relatively light roast of a long black, had some berry notes, was not too acidic.

name: Bachar Alabdullah
snippet: Nice little cafe with some really friendly staff. Coffee is really good and food was good as well. I got the eggs benny with smoked salmon; it was good but nothing special. Price is comparable to other cafes in the city but the portion size is a little on the smaller size. Overall, had a good time.

name: Mady Nortdrop
snippet: Coffee was fantastic, didn't try the food butvit did look good.

name: Diana McAuliffe
snippet: Atmosphere was lovely. Coffee not to my taste

name: V√µ Linh Nguy·ªÖn
snippet: Average coffee, average food. Lots of misleading reviews.

name: Garry Long
snippet: Food ok, service a bit off the day I visited.

name: Ramy Ibrahim
snippet: Nice cafe ,good quality breakfast

name: John Wooden
snippet: Good coffee and lunch food.

name: Michelle Levehang
snippet: Fresh food

name: Agnes Cheung
snippet: Coffee is so so....

name: F Paul
snippet: Good breakfast and very nice coffee, and staff is friendly.They open relatively early which is handy if you have a full day. There are quite a few seating inside.

name: Tanya Tang
snippet: Coffee is awesome but not hot enough. Some items in breakkie seem ready in advance, the only hot part is butterüòÇ, roughly ten-minute waiting. Waitress lady is THE BEST STAR here. Nice vibe for a relaxed beginning of a day.Good in general.

name: Bryant Chang
snippet: I love my meal, and thanks the staff hearing ‚Äú I don‚Äôt want my food with Feta cheese‚Äù and they offered me normal cheese with my omelet ‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è The coffee for me is fine, but I tried the special latte, actually the flavor were too thin, no matter green tea latte or Taro latte. Also my partner order the flat white with almond milk, the first one is quite bitter, and he gave them a second chance, and got better, so maybe need to be careful :) In short, a relax and friendly place to have brekkie!

name: Jake Brumley
snippet: Really pleasant experience from Alain, excellence customer service and great coffee. Appreciate the great experience, thank you.

name: Naomi Tobiasson
snippet: The manager is lovely, coffee is delicious. Generous breakfast size!

name: Â∞èÈ≥•ÈÅäÈæç‰πã‰ªã
snippet: First time visit of a local. Coffee - Really good batch brew. Twin Peaks Agent Cooper "damn good coffee' good. Trying V60 next time for sure. Big Breakfast - Very skillfully done poached eggs. A pleasant amount of bacon. Could definitely use some better sausages and tomato deserved more char. Service - Bubbly, friendly staff, who are very proud of what they do. These guys won't settle for anything less than perfect with their coffees. Understandably slower service during peak hours. Best to plan your visit ahead and give the staff the time they need to make your order to their high standards. I'd come here just for black coffee and maybe a dozen of poached eggs on sourdough stacked in a way that can only be described as a marvel of modern engineering. Hopefully I'd leave feeling a bit better prepared for reality.

name: Kyle Wiebe
snippet: No gluten free Banana bread but they have batch brew

name: Maggie Hathaway
snippet: Oh my gosh, visiting from Brissie and read our hotel reviews and saw this place. Quick service, I got my coffee on almond, very nice. If you have had gastric surgery, the serves are so big you can share a breakfast. I got the mushroom and spinach omelette, it was big and fluffy and came with sourdough. Unfortunately my OCD kicked in when I noticed all the lovely old books on the shelf were not in column order, but I just didn‚Äôt look at them and all was OK. Overall a great experience , lots of nice stuff in the display fridge as well

name: Adele Thornton
snippet: Great service, really good vibes and the food is genuine and delicious

name: Fiona Beasley
snippet: Very friendly. Lovely coffee. Love the onzen eggs. Had the bolognaise on toast today. Really good.

name: Flora Lau
snippet: Tiny but cosy caf√© serving surprisingly great and affordable lunch (around $10 per person). Try their spaghetti bolognese if it‚Äôs the pasta of the day on the menu, it‚Äôs simple but hearty. Ambience is great and relaxing, perfect for catching up with a pal over lunch. Only down side was the slightly long wait for the food to come, as it was during week day lunch rush hour afterall. Nonetheless the food definitely worth the wait. :) I haven‚Äôt tried their coffee yet but given my lunch experience, I‚Äôll surely go back and pay a visit.

name: Judy Kelly
snippet: Goffee was nice, bircher muesli was nice, granola nice, but they didn't offer milk to go with it. Presentation of food was good. Tried this place as it wasn't far from hotel we were staying at. Ambience was interesting, lots of old nick nacks. Think its changing ownership.

name: Vaughan Ramsey
snippet: Tucked away down a side street, this nook of a cafe is a great place to pick up a coffee. The staff are friendly, service is quick and there's a good range of niche coffee techniques on offer.

name: BitterBliss
snippet: Coffee: 5 Senses Passion: 8/10 Crema: 7/10 With new owners comes the inevitable worry about the impact on the coffee, but it seems that Joe Black has managed to make the transition and still provide a reliable source of good 5 Senses coffee. As they still have a single origin and cold drip on offer, their focus on providing a broad coffee experience to their customers is clear. I started off with their Ethiopian Kochere Yiracheffe as an espresso and was a bit underwhelmed by what it delivered. Rather than a citrusy, floral experience, I got much more of a molasses, syrupy, dark coffee. Wasn't bad, but certainly didn't taste like I'd expect from a Yiracheffe. To finish off I grabbed a mac, and think that I suffered the latte art of macs, where to make it pretty a little too much milk is added. All I can say is give me ugly looking delicious coffee any day... :-) So while the individual coffees I had today were not excellent, the staff service and attention to each coffee does promise lots of potential. With so many great cafes in this area, it is now up to them to live up to it. N.B. There is no #powerwhoring available There is no public WiFi available

name: Paul Reynolds
snippet: Location is great - gets the winter sun. Previous had been to cafe for coffee, toast and jam. That was good. However this time our group had three breakfast meals. Big Breakfast, Vegan Big Breakfast. Food was average and cold. Sort of like $12 diner value meal. Plenty of better places around

name: Jasmine K
snippet: I'm a local to the area but rarely get a chance to check out new cafes, so when I spotted a groupon deal I decided to bring my partner and I here for Sunday lunch. When we arrived, there was one man who happily gave us a table but then when we said we had a voucher he says "oh, you're one of those groupon people"... strange! Then an older lady with black here came and took my phone, scanned the voucher without even saying hello or smiling. We told her we might move and she got very annoyed with us - she was extremely rude and not welcoming at all. The food was just okay, nothing special. I'd definetly not return, there are far friendlier places around. Edit: Your negative and blame-filled response says a lot about how you treat customers. If you are going to treat Groupon holders as second class citizens, do not put out Groupon vouchers at all. We still paid money and the whole point of Groupon vouchers is to give people a chance to try out your cafe so they will then come back again and again. But your rude attitude and unfriendly welcome will deter many from returning.

name: Aaron Nolan
snippet: If I could give Kawa a zero star review, I would. My partner and I been looking forward to brunch but unfortunately for us we made the decision to dine at Kawa. On arrival we were quickly given a menu, ordered and sat back to enjoy each other's company .Our coffee came shortly afterwards and was OK. However, this was the last hint of speed and decent service we experienced. 35 minutes later and after watching another customer leave because his food had taken so long to come, I went to ask for an update on when to expect ours (this after watching people who had arrived after us receive their meals). The reply from our surly waiter was a simple "it's coming soon", delivered with a look of poorly masked disdain and haughtiness. After a further ten minutes, my partner and I had decided that by 1:55pm (a full 50+) minutes after arriving, we would simply have to leave as I am a type one diabetic and had taken insulin for the meal but much to our relief (albeit short lived), our food finally arrived, delivered with a furtive apology for it's lateness (which I would classify as the understatement of the year). I should have known better though. If only the food had made up for the appalling wait and waiter. My partner had ordered the open sandwich with cheese and tomato. What came out from the kitchen was a beige horror with barely melted cheese on top of tomato. I can only assume they'd used a 50 watt lightbulb which is why it took 55 minutes to prepare and had no hint of grilling in sight. I ordered a big breakfast with haloumi. The haloumi was the best bit (presumably because they didn't make it) and the rest wasn't the worst I've had in a caf√© but the mushrooms were wet and flavourless, the bacon fatty, the eggs over cooked and the tomato a soggy mess that reminded me of over cooked cauliflower you had a kid which disintegrates into mush when the air brushes over it. We left shortly after and received no further apology for the wait (which was never flagged to us). Nor was there any kind of gesture made as an apology. This wasn't surprising but perhaps two free coffees would have been possible? Again, I should have known better... The person who I assume was the owner was infinitely more apologetic than his waiter but despite this, being in my 30s, I'll simply never have the time to attend Kawa for a meal again.

name: Russell Bumak
snippet: Staff said that 3 minutes, and the manager said and staff will ready but I wait food until 35 minutes isn‚Äôt ready and this second times happened. I don‚Äôt back here again, supposed to be ask us before will ready food an hour.

name: Lucien Schneller
snippet: Average coffee, terrible food, awful service. I've only been once (last week), but won't be going back. We ordered take away, and then were never called when it was ready. Eventually went to the counter to ask where it was and it was sitting on the counter, our food lukewarm. We ordered a bacon and egg sandwich and banana bread. The sandwich was not toasted, cold bread that seemed to be from the supermarket, the bacon was soggy and only just cooked, and they also decided to include cold spinach in the sandwich - not sure why. The banana bread was also soggy, and smothered in butter - again could have got better from the supermarket over the road. With so many good cafes in Surry Hills, I'm not sure how this place is still going.

name: Mariana Silva
snippet: I do not recommend this place. had the worst costumer service because I had a Groupon Voucher. They wouldn't let me sit because I was 10 min earlier for my booking. Place was still empty anyways. had to leave since I felt horrible. It is a shame, the place is right in front of my business, I was a regular and also sent all my clients there. NOT ANYMORE.

name: Anon Omouse
snippet: Served breakfast with big hair in it. Asked for a new one....5 mins later served me the same plate of food, cold but minus the hair. Chef then came out and tried to blame someone else because the hair was blonde and also claimed that it was a fresh plate. It wasn't. Then when challenged the the eggs, avocado and Rosti where the same, she finally admitted she changed only the parts on the plate that she believed the hair had touched. The hair was everywhere...Haha. So gross....Seriously poor kitchen but kind and understanding wait staff. Going to find it really hard to ever go back.

name: Dave H
snippet: Rudest, least interested staff of any cafe we visit in Surry Hills.Way better alternatives nearby are Mr Mo, Concrete Duck, La Mish.... they appreciate their customers along with great food and coffee!

name: SK West
snippet: Took 50 minutes for our food to come. The food was cold when it arrived, tomatoes were soggy, mushrooms flavourless. I don‚Äôt know how they survive and people go back.

name: molnex11
snippet: I just had a home delivery of a so called Minestroni soup and a Watermelons salad.This was the worst food and value ever.The only good new is that the portions are very small.

name: Gerry North
snippet: Coffee like warm milk, lemonade is just water and juice at $5.50, Poached eggs hard boiled, inedible toasted club sandwich, wrong juice brought twice, 2 x rude staff, What's there to like.

name: Veronica Lin
snippet: Good atmosphere , terrible food!! Ordered chicken ball -- it came up with the center still cold (supposed to be hot), disgusting. Good service and friendly staff.

name: Rudy Benhamou
snippet: Staff is always changing. They're just using people to throw them out. They're not nice. Moreover, I would say there is a very bad organization inside of the restaurant.

name: Elis Zot
snippet: the worst cafe in Surry hills, service was poor ,and about the food not comment......

name: Marconi Robertson
snippet: Rude slow service, average to below average food and watch out for surcharge

name: Gianni Longo
snippet: HORRIBLE DISGUSTING SERVICE AND PORTIONS ARE A RIP OFF

name: Lyrin Brooks
snippet: Yuck.

name: Andrew Pickles
snippet: This place is awful.

name: Tara Redmond
snippet: This cafe has lost it's way. I had been going here for approx 20 years but the recent (year or so) change of ownership has seen the quality of the food on the infamous and long standing menu decrease and the relaxed cafe vibe disappear. Instead the focus appears less on the food & vibe and more on the bottom dollar. The final straw: we had just started our coffee and were waiting for breakfast to arrive when the staff member (owner?) asked us to fix up the bill - he then appeared rather annoyed when we requested to sort at the end of our meal. Farewell old friend, we won't be returning.

name: Julien Charton
snippet: Juices are good but the food is not what is use to be (I think they change the cook). It is way too expensive for what it is and customer service is terrible. There are a lot of good places on crown st. Kawa is not one of them.

name: Rod Jones
snippet: Serving little marionette coffee which is a great Roastery... Yet somehow they were still able to make the coffee taste like truck stop coffee.... And poorly textured milk made it even worse... The actual cafe fitout is still has that beautiful Byron bay feel to it but sorry guys you really need to get your coffee game upto scratch

name: Lenny Tjam
snippet: Cute place but if you are looking for those moist, indulgent type of brownies, avoid these ones.. Probably they are the healthier version 'cos the whole Cafe appears to be more 'health-oriented'. PS: To the owner: I can't respond to your message somehow... But yes, we ordered two of them and finished them, but that's because we don't like to waste food.. :) To be fair, yes, maybe I am over generalising in my earlier feedback, hence I have edited it to be clearer... :)

name: Kumi Taguchi
snippet: Was looking forward to my special brew of lemon, ginger and honey. Maybe it's the word 'brew' that got me - thinking it would be something house made. Unfortunately, it was basically hot water with a few bits of lemon and cut up ginger and a bit of honey. A shame because it's a nice spot.

name: Martin Varga
snippet: Little Marionette beans made into delicious coffee, nice spot with outside seating, very warm during sunny winter days. However the food was mediocre at best. Their chicken meatball meals are OK. But Club sandwich was pretty bad. Especially the dry chicken meat must have spent at least two days in the fridge to taste that bad.

name: Angie Lowe
snippet: Clean flavors, fresh food and alot to choose from on menu. Great for vegetarians as well. Lovely atmosphere to sit and have a coffee, my coffee was a little bit weak for a large. Good value breakfast with generous slices of delicious grainy bread. I had roasted pumpkin, feta and saut√©ed mushrooms on toast. Yum! Only the coffee let the place down for me. I would give Kawa almost 4 stars.

name: Tom Wright
snippet: Nice Cafe especially if you can get a table on the street. Food is varied and the frappacino is excellent! If you order eggs, ask for them runny (if you like that) as they tend to hard boil them, though I suspect that's highly dependant on the chef!

name: Kristin Sutter
snippet: Has really gone down in terms of service and food quality. I'm not sure if there was a change in ownership or kitchen, but overall not what it used to be. They lost our food order the last time we were there and when the food came an hour later, it was cold with not much apology.

name: Ryan Irons
snippet: Okay, not great. Staff ignored me so I had to get up and order. Poached eggs were fully boiled. No water ever came out even though the guy said he would bring out a bottle. #firstworldproblems

name: Gavin E. Thomas
snippet: Food was good, however got awkward when the manager was yelling at staff for seating guests.

name: Ted Crosby
snippet: Staff are lovely and helpful. Food and coffee is ok.

name: Frank Farrelly
snippet: For was nice but pricy and prices charged did not match menu.

name: Sylvain Aimoz
snippet: One of those "Surrey hills' caf√©", a bit old fashion in a good way, original products to try..

name: Maximillion L
snippet: Kwila is hidden away at the bottom of the hill on Foster Street. If you were unfamiliar with this area you might be like me, heading the wrong way uphill towards Hunt Street, as the bottom part of the street looked like the back of the other buildings. Of course silly me, I should have checked the map. Kwila is a cute little cafe, probably more suitable for takeaway coffee and sweets. Great if you were a vegan or vegetarian, their simple offerings seemed to be all vegetarian, at least today they were. We turned up at 11:30am based on the great reviews on Google and here. Their vegan pies and two salads (no meat) on offer today were not ready. We were told a 10 minutes wait for the pumpkin soup and toast. We didn't mind waiting while having our coffee. We were actually after something a little more substantial but that will do for now as we were feeling cold and hungry. They do have a small table at the back in the corner. Two persons can sit up at the corner wall sides. The rest are a few low wooden cubes along the narrow wall. And two stools at the front window. The people were friendly, the coffee were great, probably one of the best tasting in Sydney. The homemade pumpkin soup was also tasty, I like the fact that no cream were added. I guess they used spices like cumin and turmeric, there were also roasted pumpkin seeds. It was a great health choice. I would come again for their coffee and soup if I happened to be around this area but I probably won't make a special trip like today.

name: Tony Goh
snippet: Good coffee, a bit on the acid side, but full flavour, robust. Good service. Hole in the wall and hidden further boosts it's charm and appeal.

name: Timothy Vandeputte
snippet: Great coffee but No WiFi...

name: suria jin
snippet: Bit sour coffee. Nice place.

name: Coco and Vine (Coco & Vine)
snippet: Kwila is a true treasure for the urban culinary explorer. Outstanding coffee paired with simply great food makes this cafe one to add to the list for any true foodie. We tried the cold drip, chai, flat white, Sunrise Bowl, and smashed avo and every one of them was top notch. The space is eclectic, warm, and welcoming.

name: Fraulein Maria
snippet: The coffee here is amazing and well worth a visit just for this however the staff here are also super friendly and the avo on toast is one of my favourite things

name: Grant D
snippet: If you're after consistently great coffee and fantastic service look no further. I stumbled across this little gem back in January and can say it's been my go to coffee shop ever since. Even though I haven't had a chance to taste the food, colleagues can't get enough of their avo on toast or their delicious home-made soups. The fact that it's tucked away only adds to its character. If you haven't gone out it on the coffee list, oh and remember to take your own cup to get a discounted coffee.....

name: Tim Walter
snippet: Brilliant coffee and the people here are super nice. They roast their own and whenever I can I buy the whole beans for the machine at home which, has produced some brilliant shots. My personal fave in Surry Hills!

name: Sam Elliott
snippet: Pretty much the perfect coffee stop. Staff are lovely, know and their stuff, and are generally great people. Coffee and food is top-notch.

name: dave pigram
snippet: Great coffee, awesome 'sunrise bowl' and the nicest people you could ever hope to meet!

name: J Choi
snippet: Awesome coffee everytime, avo toast is a must try and friendly staff :)

name: Joanne Mackay
snippet: Excellent coffee and 50c off when you bring your own cup!

name: Karri Griffin
snippet: Best cafe on the street! Delicious food + coffee complimented by an amazing service.

name: Larissa Jaffe
snippet: Amazing coffee and they sell Funky Pies! So good!

name: Vijay Raghavan
snippet: Best coffee I've had in Sydney. Awesome crew!

name: Max Mullen
snippet: Best coffee near Central, excellent and friendly service.

name: David Wright
snippet: Cheaper with a Keep Cup. A great ethical place to get your coffee

name: T Callaghan
snippet: Great coffee + a lot of love, backed by an amazing soundtrack.

name: Alessandro Belgiorno-Nettis
snippet: Wonderful people and a cosy, relaxed little shop. Kokomo smoothie is a must!

name: LL W
snippet: Great coffee with nice people in an out-of-the-way location.

name: Tom
snippet: Acai free Acai bowl. They claim a full brick was used and yet there is no acai taste or colour at all. A bland oat bowl.The wait staff were fairly nice but offered no help. The kitchen lady takes no pride in her job. Directly stated that she put "a lot" of acai in, yet there was no taste

name: kathryn rose
snippet: I paid $7 for Vegemite toast(the man explained its an extra $1.50 for gluten free bread) which came out with Vegemite barley spread onto only half of my slices. I spoke to the man who served me who offered no acknowledgment or apology, he just stared at me blankly and said '....so you want extra butter and Vegemite?'. This is what I got back. (Won't be going back because it's clear that the kitchen and the man serving people are taking the piss)

name: Ainsley M
snippet: Was having a lovely breakfast with a friend when a reservation ticket for 10mins time was plonked down on our table without even looking at us, let alone any conversation. So rude. How to make customers feel unwelcome in one easy lesson.

name: Brendan Hong
snippet: Quite possibly the worst dinner I've had in a long time - Ordered the Katsu burger and a side of sweet chilli chicken wings. My mate separately ordered the pulled pork burger. My mates burger came out in about 5 minutes, which is fine as i assume the pulled pork is already cooked, and they need to fry the Katsu. But about 30 minutes later, i was still waiting for both the burger and the wings. Went to to the counter to check, and they said 'it's just getting plated now'.. so i went back to my table. 15 minutes later, frustrated, i walk back to the counter to see my burger and wings sitting on the counter waiting for the one barman/waiter to be available to serve it (he was taking drink orders at the bar). Food was served cold, no apologies were received, definitely not worth a 45 minute wait. I blame the fact that there was only one person on service, which is shocking for an establishment such as Blacksmith.

name: yflorence
snippet: Worse customer service experience. I waited 5 mins to order a coffee and a toastie...so far I have waited other 20 mins for a toastie...still not here.. where is my take away!! Will not come back!!!

name: M C
snippet: Ordered a chop chop avo with quinoa and caramelised onions - absolutely worse brunch I have ever had. I have ordered the same dish three times - and each time they have just reduced the amount of quinoa and avo and increased the onions. The dish should really be called "chop chop onions" - there's hardly any avocado and quinoa on there, the onions do not go well with avocado and quinoa. Will not be back.

name: Karel Herink
snippet: The willingness of the staff to serve me a stale (re-heated) croissant at 7:30AM this morning ruined my takeaway breakfast. Other than that the coffee is on par with other places in the area. #toughasnails

name: Paul Osullivan
snippet: Bought 6 Large Coffees in takeaway cups. They were $5.20 each.

name: Nitya Raghavan
snippet: Overpriced food that wasn't worth it.

name: Ritu Sangwan
snippet: Worst coffee ....

name: Amanda Fallon
snippet: It was a shame it wasn't open

name: Justin Medcalf
snippet: Take away hot chocolate served cold and tea was more like water with milk - not great!! Decor is awesome hence the extra star

name: Craige Riley
snippet: Better options in the area, poor staff service. Won't go back

name: juraj kosnar
snippet: ordinary place but looks good

name: Marta Citterico
snippet: Another hipster cafe

name: Keestu Tappali Ekanathan
snippet: Super oily burger with good beer. The ambience is unique indeed.

name: Andy Lai
snippet: Nice pies but dining in a little expensive. For example the pie by itself takeaway is $8 but to dine in with salad it's 14.5! 6.5 more for some salad on the side...

name: Kirsty Wong
snippet: my 2nd time visit didn't have the wow factor of food and service anymore ordered pizza and bulgogi bowl pizza was just alright unfortunately bulgogi bowl is tasteless ended up paid $41 not sure if that was the correct amount either

name: myles lc
snippet: Coffee is good. Food is OK. Location is OK. The theme is heavy industrial/black smith (hence the name) but that can get a little tiring. I come here semi regularly and (first world problem alert) it's a bit of a pain that when you finish a sit down coffee when it comes to pay you need to line up with all the other people who are ordering their take away coffee!!!!

name: Tracy Wang
snippet: The breakfast and lunch menu offers a good selection of dishes to choose from, while the breakfast dishes we had weren't a standout, the lunch menu did look good. Coffee is from Toby‚Äôs Estate and cold drip and pour-over are on offer should you feel like it. We went on a Sunday for a late brunch, it wasn't overly busy but the service was a bit slow, we had to wave down a staff after waiting for more than 10mins to get service.

name: Kathleen Szabo
snippet: Extra $1 for soy for any ‚Äòlarge‚Äô drink. Bought an iced chocolate on a hot day and was pretty surprised to pay an extra dollar for soy. This would really put me off buying coffee/brewed chai here in the morning. I‚Äôve never encountered this anywhere else? Maybe it‚Äôs the Surry Hills surcharge? Instead I‚Äôd head somewhere that charges the regular 50c flat. Regardless of that. I like the place and the drink was good.

name: Em Dido
snippet: The interior decor is the drawing card of this chic cafe on Chalmers Street, which is something that I am willing to pay a little more on their food to come here and ogle at their unique design (steampunkish? industrial meets farm??). Food is so-so but the interesting experience made up for the lack of flavour. Worth going there for a coffee.

name: Nardee W
snippet: Great vibes. Dissapointed with the Wagu burger.

name: Mark O
snippet: A nice cafe with a good theme. If you want a large mug coffee forget it. Big cup is not big if size matters.

name: Justin Walker
snippet: Nice decor, okay coffee (on the milky side with slightly muted flavour) and good service.

name: glyn suller
snippet: Good looking cafe. I've only had coffee here so can't comment on food.

name: Stan Hofer
snippet: Coffee and hot chocolate was okay, croissant not that fresh Unfortunately.

name: Jeremie Granat
snippet: Pretty expensive but with great alternative choices of breakfast meals

name: Michael Leaney
snippet: A little expensive, and I don't really like the options.Kind of cool decor though.

name: Gooner Pak
snippet: It's called Blacksmith roasters yet they use Toby's estate, it's misleading and inaccurate.

name: Kaz a'Wary
snippet: Interesting place with very steam punk feel.

name: Fran√ßoise Coirier
snippet: OK food slow service

name: Serene W
snippet: Poor custom service. Wasn't asked if I wanted sugar in my latte. So when I went back to ask them to make a new one after taking a sip. They took the previous one away and asked me to pay for another one.

name: Rachel Sang
snippet: Not same as the menu, and did not reminder me before the payment. I bought matcha fondant set which includes fondant, tea and ice cream, but I got fondant only. So I returned it. Bad experience, and matcha Swiss roll is not good as expected. Quite disappointed.

name: L
snippet: Personally the matcha is very weak for my tastes. The cookies are decent.

name: Kiki
snippet: The taste was good, but the customer service was poor. I went alone and the cashier was abrupt and answered my question very absentmindedly. After finishing the purchase, the moment I walked out of the store, a Western guest came in behind me and I could finally see the bright smile of the staff.

name: ling shadow
snippet: Quality dropped;( it was excellent before ...went there at 2:40 and kitchen was closed already ...very disappointed ...came all the way for very bad quality food ...

name: Alecia Chen
snippet: Had been lining for 15 minutes, then when it got to me it was 3:03. They said the kitchen closes at 3 so I can't order. Really?Food is delicious though

name: Y M.
snippet: It's a nice cafe if the staff is more friendly... JP staff was unkind and unfriendly unfortunately. Matcha Latte and roll cake were very very nice.

name: Jessica Wu
snippet: A tiny Japanese cafe specialises in green matcha cakes and beverages. We tried the matcha swiss role and tart and they were nice and not overly sweet, typical of Japanese desserts which I like. The downside is that the place is very small with very limited tables and seats on offer for patrons to dine in. And the seats were low stools so not the most comfy and definitely not young family friendly. We got take away.

name: Ìô©ÎØºÏ£º
snippet: it is good very good. but the table is too low, i just think about how to eat clearly, so i just dont remember how that dessert was. and the black current macaroon is too sweet. i think i need to try the other things. anyway the only problrm is the table

name: MCG Francis
snippet: A matcha place like you would never imagine. The pastries were awesome, I have just a bit of an issue with the Matcha Tea Latte. I don‚Äôt know why it taste like a seaweed of some sort which I don‚Äôt like. Probably for some, it‚Äôs good, not for my taste. We ordered Cheesecake and Apple Muffin which were really good. The tables and chairs might not suit a larger or a taller person so hopefully, they can have a proper one.

name: Zen Celeste
snippet: Great breakfast and Japanese latte. Only thing is that chairs and tables are not designed for you to sit and enjoy the food, guaranteed back pain if you try to finish the sandwich and coffee. Understand it is a small cafe at the back of ally with winter wind, so take away if you can. Don't expect to sit comfortablely for a brunch.

name: Cam Law
snippet: Really limited seats. Plain water available. The chiffon cake is average but the others are great. Last time went to the cafe and the staff forgot our drinks but we got refund.

name: Mimi Lu
snippet: Great green tea desserts and drinks with really good matcha powder. Only thing is that it has really limited seating so maybe grab one on the go.

name: Miffy
snippet: Bit slow service and over price. But tasty drinks&sandwiches

name: Suresh Kerai
snippet: Nice coffee and asian inspired sweet treats. Recommend the homemade Banana Bread.

name: sugarpuffi yin
snippet: has the most extensive and gourmet macarons range but also comes with a ridiculous price tag of $2.70 for the tiniest macaron

name: YIDI TIAN
snippet: Lovely desserts but too sweet for me.

name: J C
snippet: Average coffee, average food and average customer service. Was expecting more...

name: Denise (Dee)
snippet: Seatinf is cramped. But nice matcha deserts

name: Paula Vigeant
snippet: Good coffee... interesting menu

name: Flora Lau
snippet: Interesting green tea drinks.

name: Ruby Lin
snippet: (Translated by Google) Coffee was too watery, the smell and the flavors couldn't come out, not fresh enough. Wasn't impressed by the cake roll nor the muffin neither, the color was right though the matcha flavor is very weak. It's just a OK cafe , overrated. The coffee is not fragrant and the taste is very light. It may be that too much water is added, which caused me to go to the alley next door and buy a small latte to add caffeine. The cake rolls are ordinary, muffins are also popular, and the cake body has no matcha aroma. The cake was tasteless, and the coffee was tasteless, which made me think I had a problem with my taste. After I bought the coffee in the alley next door, I confirmed that my taste was normal. It's just an ordinary coffee shop, well-known. (Original) Coffee was too watery, the smell and the flavors couldn't come out, not fresh enough. Wasn't impressed by the cake roll nor the muffin neither, the color was right though the matcha flavor is very weak. It's just a OK cafe, overrated.
