name: Carrie Chi
snippet: I am so happy to find the shop that the hojicha Swiss cake is not too sweet and the genmaicha latte is good flavor. It seems that I arrive to Kyoto in a moment.

name: Sheldon C
snippet: Went to this place on the recommendation of a friend. Had the matcha Swiss roll and matcha latte. They were both delicious. Nice bitter notes of matcha in the cake balanced out by a creamy matcha cream. Liked that the cake wasn‚Äôt too sweet. The matcha latte was also great and also not too sweet. The cafe itself is quite small and tucked away down a smaller street which gave it an industrial ambiance. Staff were very friendly and attentive. Make sure you have cash if you‚Äôre going to spend less than $20 cause they have a $20 minimum for credit card (not sure about EFTPOS).

name: IS L
snippet: Tiny little shop in the mildly of CBD with lots of match goodies. Limited seatings, takeaway available. Very nice match flavors and dessert, savory dishes from next table also look good.

name: huoshan W
snippet: cafe is too watery. the pastry are worth trying. Sandwich is so so. Good place for afternoon tea with one or two friends. Not suitable for groups with more ppl. It‚Äôll be too crowded. Not difficult to find the cafe if you follow the google map.

name: Phoebe L
snippet: Bustling vibe with many local workers coming in for their coffee fix / food, or a business meeting. Very smooth creamy coffee, super friendly staff. Small but very well considered menu with a selection of pasta / salads / wraps / sandwiches in the display for a quick lunch takeaway. Very reasonable prices too. Great little joint - keep up the good work!

name: Jean-Philippe S.Duc
snippet: Best caf√© on this little strip IMHO. I get my morning coffee with a smile, brekky or lunch with fresh tasty ingredients (loads of variety) and now been grabbing a dinner pack if I know I‚Äôll have no time to cook! Highly recommended üéâ

name: Ibrahim El Badawi
snippet: Lovely place for good coffee and smiley service!

name: O Hayashi
snippet: Do yourself a favor and visit this lovely cafe. Happy vibes and always greeted with big smile. Makes you feel extremely valued. The service is unmatched. The staff truly cares about your experience. The food is absolutely amazing ‚Äì fresh and delicious. Highly recommend! The best campos coffee and fastest service in surry hills!~

name: An Dang
snippet: Bustling coffee establishment in Surry Hills. Fantastic coffee, fantastic service.. very cramped but suits the feel of the cafe.

name: Yuval Pilavsky
snippet: Excellent food, friendly service. Highly recommended üòä

name: Ellehcore Daiko
snippet: Amazingly tasty food at a great price and beautiful staff who are lovely to talk to. Thankyou for a great meal!

name: Stephanie Iveson
snippet: Friendly service, good food selection and very flexible! There chips are lovely and the brownie that I was given with my coffee. Pleasure for lunch!

name: Kirsten Sterling
snippet: Reliably good coffee, and friendly staff. There is often a queue but they work fast to get you a caffeine fix!

name: Maliha Khan
snippet: Citta has been my go-to coffee place for about a year now. I love Campos coffee, but the bigger reason I kept going back to them for my daily dose of caffeine is their service. The staff there is very friendly and makes the morning coffee pick-me-up even more special. I quite enjoy their croissants, berry muffins and tuna wrap as well!

name: Amy Teri
snippet: Hadn't visited this place before but it always looked busy so I thought I would give it a go. I went for the Chicken & Mushroom Risotto. After ordering, I was watching and realised that it was stored in a plastic container in the viewing fridge therefore not cooked fresh to order (probably wouldn't of ordered it if I'd have known it was just going to get heated up from the container). The risotto was probably one of the worst I have tasted. It was bland with no seasoning whatsoever and extremely mushy. It was the taste and consistency of baby food. I took it back and the manager was kind enough to refund me. Nevertheless I probably won't be back anytime soon. Perhaps they were having an off day?

name: Glenda Butler
snippet: I take my coffee very serious and these guys know how to get it right every time. The food is always fresh and service second to none. The entirety of experience sets the vibe for each day! Love your work Citta!

name: Kevin Fleming
snippet: Funky cafe on Holt Street in the heart of Surry Hills. Very popular for morning coffee - well- because it's great. Was uninspired by the breakfast offering - interesting concept of no menu - just order what you want. The breakfast itself of toast / poached eggs / ham / mushroom / spinach was ok - but nothing to rave over. Great coffee.

name: Lionel Rudolph
snippet: Great coffee and great customer service the best

name: Amelia R
snippet: Felt compelled to write after visiting this morning. Ordered a cappuccino, and a latte was brought to my table, so I said it wasn't mine to the waitress. She returned 10 sec later with the same latte with chocolate powder on it. I asked for an actual cappuccino instead - it arrived 20 secs later having been poured into a cappuccino cup. Needless to say, by this stage, it didn't taste very good. Admittedly it was a busy time for the cafe, but that's just lazy and disrespectful. I was really polite at the time but realised later what appalling service I'd had!

name: N Gibbins
snippet: Tiny, Trendy and Tasty I love Citta Cafe in Surry Hills. The service is amazing and they always remember what I have. Not enough cafes care about the quality of their coffee and food, I personally think it's the best around. Judging by how many people go out of their way to visit Cafe Citta proves how good it is.

name: Ashley Johnston
snippet: Staff are incredible and so friendly and warm! Always put a smile on my face during covid! Thanks lovely team üòÉ

name: Chris Hubble
snippet: Best coffee in Surry Hills, super tasty and strong.Bacon and egg roll was a let down though, good value at $6.50 but was pre prepared and looked like it had been cooked in a sandwich press

name: andrea lau
snippet: Have worked in the area for 5+ years and could always rely on Citta for pasta, amazing salads, a great burrito and soups, as well as the arvo sweet fix. I loved that fridge if stuff you could see and pick and choose. Lovely staff. Recommend the satay noodle salad and if you ever chance upon the pea mint orecchiette on the specials you must order it.

name: Amber Gastin
snippet: Best cafe in Surry Hills. Super speedy, personalised service - they knew my name and how I liked my coffee within the first week and it's never too much trouble for them to whip up something that's not already on the menu. Keep up the good work guys üòä

name: Karen Leung
snippet: The best service you will get in a cafe this size. What they lack in floor space they highly compensate in food quality and service. The food are far more better than other cafes in the hood plus the choices provided are impressive. This place is always busy for many reasons!!

name: Tye Porteous
snippet: Good coffee, small size

name: KP
snippet: One of the friendliest staff you can meet. Olie even remembers her customers' names. Hot chocolate is amazing and so is the food!

name: Kris Pantovic
snippet: just had a specially crafted char grilled vegetable focaccia. absolutely delicious. my taste buds danced all the way back to Italy

name: Christine Lasker
snippet: Had the Best Corn Cakes Tomato Relish & Rocket with Chicken today!!!!!! Brett you're on fire! Love Missy Chrissy xxx Thursday 7 Jan - I am soooo missing you guys!!!! Please tell me you are back on Monday 11 January 2016! Missy Chrissy xxx

name: Tara Richardson
snippet: Awesome cafe, coffee is best in the area by far. The staff were very helpful and friendly, I would recommend this cafe to all my friends

name: Stan Bozhkov
snippet: One of my favourite cafes in the area. Everyone is so kind. Always. It's not a surprise that there's a queue so often. Don't get scared of it though. It clears pretty quickly.

name: Peter Baron
snippet: This cafe is amazing. Any quicker service and it would be on the table before you know what you want! (and that's just about everything) great Decaf.!

name: Sam Leckie
snippet: Great coffee and great staff! The food is of a really high quality, the only complaint I have is that there is no gluten free option.

name: Toby Olsen
snippet: Strong delicious coffee. Best in Surry Hills. Today the coffee wasn't as strong as it has been recently but perhaps a one off.

name: Quazi Haque
snippet: Great for lunch, daily specials changing regularly, always something new to try. Very friendly staff.

name: Brett Dickinson
snippet: Lovely friendly staff, great coffee, amaaaaazing coconut bread and top sandwiches

name: iosif kalitzakis
snippet: That‚Äôs the best CAFE in the Area by far from the second. Coffee made by Matt was like drinking nectar of the GodsüëåüèΩüëåüèΩ

name: Annie Piper
snippet: The best coffee, service, food and value. Every single time.

name: Bryden McLeod
snippet: Great 'hole in the wall' coffee joint, staff are down to earth and lovely, try the breakfast wrap.

name: Graciela Olivares
snippet: Love this place! My spot every morning to start the day with a delicious coffee and a big smile!

name: Benjamin Chen
snippet: Very Good food options. Coffees... Okay :P ... Very very friendly staffs.

name: Joshua Price
snippet: Food isnt stored properly, nor do they throw anything out - instead they wait until its purchased by poor customers - BE careful.

name: Claire G
snippet: Small cafe with about 4 or 5 tables churning out good coffee for the local office crowd

name: Nicholas Fonseca
snippet: Fast, friendly, service with a smile. Always happy to support these guys.

name: Bobby's Corner
snippet: good service unfortunately coffee only 2 out of 10

name: Kris Pantovic
snippet: Superior services, great aroma, sublime coffee, great food choices

name: Symon Peters
snippet: Cool little Surry Hills cafe... Very local atmosphere and great food of course!

name: James Casey
snippet: Great coffee. Great food. Great service.

name: Sabrina Beydoun
snippet: Super quick and great coffee!

name: James Ducker
snippet: Great Campos coffee and almond croissants

name: Mark Richardson
snippet: Best coffee and croissants in Sydney

name: Peter Godfrey
snippet: delicious coffee good service

name: Ho-Yan Shum
snippet: Good local coffee place

name: Christopher Emerzidis
snippet: Always a good experience

name: Chao Wang
snippet: Food was ok, but expect to get your order for 40min. An old woman asked how was the meal when checked out, I was being super polite and honest to compliment food first then said a bit long wait for the food. Surprisingly, the old waitress with purple dye on hair said in a loud voice, our food are freshly made, so 40min wait is normal üò§. I was hoping she at least apologised for a bit, but this was the attitude I got. After a few hours I still keep thinking of how rude she was. I checked the google rating before going to this cafe and rating 4.5 is really not bad. However, 4 is for the food we had (Cok Madame and Zucchini fritter), and 0 for the old waitress‚Äôs attitude. So it‚Äôs for sure I‚Äôll never come back again, and i wish you keep the waiting time longer and longer üòÇ

name: scubii steve
snippet: I have been to so many cafes in my travels..and I am one of THOSE people who likes things just 'SO'... as for this cafe I can honestly say... WOW... WOW.... WOW.. the meals are just the right size leaving you fulfilled and the amazing thought out flavour combinations are just mind blowing eg.. rose water shots with a breakfast dish... WHAT!!!!! The bar has been set for quality and quantity at this very clean and tidy cafe.. with a very inclusive multicultural atmosphere the cafe really is my pic of Sydney's cafes...stop in and say hello you will love it.. ( I am no way associated with this cafe except for loving the place) pics provided is my meal...

name: Gagan Jalandhra
snippet: Attentive, friendly staff - provided us with blankets when it got cold outside. A little pricey, but food was great. Good cocktails

name: Sophie Bex
snippet: Had a wonderful brunch on Sunday afternoon here, highly recommended. The cafe was very busy when we arrived however was greeted promptly by a lovely blonde guy who got us a table right away. Took our complicated coffee order and juices by memory and came out promptly and correct I was impressed. He also informed us there was a 30min wait on food which was fantastic to know. A few minutes after receiving our drinks he returned to take our food orders and was very informative about the menu, and was able to cater for my dietary needs, food came out in about 25minutes and tasted amazing A+++ to the chef. After finishing we went to the counter to pay and was very happy to be-able to split our bill. Multiply staff thanked us for coming as well left. Definitely will go back

name: Rebekah Thompson
snippet: good food gorgeous aesthetic and sweet staff (just needs free wifi so we can study!) i got the bacon and egg roll and it was so good one of the best i have ever had $13 but expensive for a bacon and egg roll but worth it and delish campos coffee cappuccino :) friend got a large latte and a salmon and cream cheese bagel w spinach also loved and was only $7.5!

name: Angela Conn
snippet: Amazing quality brunch and coffee. I had the greek eggs and loved loved loved it. Space and staff are welcoming. Relaxed local vibe, despite how popular this place is. nice to see this long-term Surry favourite is still going strong and quality is 2 thumbs up.

name: Ed Madon
snippet: One of the best coffees in Sydney, in a bright and inviting space, with a fantastic menu. The truffle scrambled eggs and chorizo were cooked perfectly and the burger was delicious. The fresh juices are a must try as well.

name: Paolo Villacarlos
snippet: This is actually a really solid spot to eat. Situated at the top of Bourke Street just below Oxford, it‚Äôs a natural convergence between Surry Hills, Paddington, and Darlinghurst. There are always a lot of outdoor seats in the mini-square and along the sidewalk. Even on Mother‚Äôs Day we were able to get a table for two immediately without a reservation. In a way it might even be too much seating‚Äîdidn‚Äôt totally feel like I had a comfortable amount of space so I docked one star for that. It is certainly dog-friendly in that you can have your pup with you, but didn‚Äôt see much water bowls being offered out to the pups. And on more than one occasion we overheard or saw a dog at another table getting a little excited at the proximity of other dogs be it at neighboring tables or just passing close by on the street. I went with the fried chicken burger with kimchi and chips and it was very satisfying. The fried chicken skin was satisfyingly crunchy, and the kimchi, while messy, was undoubtedly delicious, and I don‚Äôt even like kimchi that much (gasp!). Partner had a tuna Ni√ßoise salad and I was surprised that it was served on a bed of beans, olives, potatoes, and something green like an olive with a stem. I‚Äôm not a fan of olives, but my partner found it to be quite good, and filling‚Äîwe ended up taking some of it away with us. And honorable mention for being adjacent to Lavie & Belle. The bakery right next door added the irresistible fragrance of freshly baked bread to our dining experience, and if I wasn‚Äôt so full after my burger I would have definitely picked up some croissants for dessert.

name: duality
snippet: Modern chic cafe in the bustling north end of Surry Hills. Nice outdoor seating area. Good range of options on the menu. Went for the Mac daddy croissant. Mac and cheese super lush and bacon nice and crispy. Food probably came out a bit on slow side..but overall a good place for Sunday brunch.

name: Francesca K
snippet: I can't help but call out the incorrect review below. No one has been more careful and COVID safe than the team at Lumiere and it's purely unlucky they had a case there through no fault of their own.. I'm there every morning for my coffee and bacon and egg roll and the staff are ALWAYS masked (including the barista mentioned below), sanitising tables, sanitising menus, making sure people check in and doing all they can. They're a highlight of surry hills and the abundance of positive reviews speak for themselves. KEEP UP THE GOOD WORK !!

name: Captain kranq
snippet: On the Burke St Cycleway and a stone throw from Taylor Square . Has good coffee and is great for people watching. It has a wrap around inside outside seating so you can chase the sun or avoid it. A comfortable feel and attentive staff make for a pleasant experience. I only get coffee and Vegimite toast and it always comes with real butter and plenty of it for the thick cut bread that is always perfectly toasted. Sorry about the food picture.. but is was so good I had to eat it directly ... There is always a rainbow flag out the front too. üòÄ ((Amended... I think it's been sold... The mood was .. 'shut up customer . Your always wrong'. Can't say the experience was good. Because of a dramatic non binary person who works there being a tad too dramatic)). Pity really.. the coffee was ok

name: Amy Lou
snippet: Lumiere is a solid representation of what makes Aussie brunch great. Friendly staff, delicious Campos coffee, dog friendly and does a smashing smashed avo. Their ricotta hotcakes are a must try fan-favourite, paired with fresh juices that tastes like summer in a cup. Reasonable prices for the serving sizes and quality of food. Indoor and outdoor seating allows for larger groups and they split bills. I always look forward to visiting when in Sydney.

name: Kurt Poniewierka
snippet: How do you make eggs benedict better, add some pork belly with crispy crackling. The staff here are always super friendly and your dog is welcome

name: Gemma A
snippet: I was disappointed by my $20 ($18 for the toast and $2 per egg) avocado smash toast. The toast was so thin and dry it wasn't very enjoyable and there was hardly any avocado at all. This was pretty terrible value for money. I did see some other dishes that looked amazing so I think this place is just about ordering the right dish. The omelette on our table was also overdone and not nice. I think the avo smash could have been improved by being more generous with the thickness of the bread and the amount of avocado. The coffee was great and the staff were very friendly. I'd go back and try find one of the 'great' dishes üôÇ

name: George Mellick
snippet: My partner and I are locals and we regularly go to Lumiere for their delicious breakfasts and lunches. Not only is the location amazing, with lots of sunshine and (dog friendly) outdoor seating, but the personal service from the friendly young staff keeps us coming back. If you are in the area we would thoroughly recommend you stop in for a meal or just a quality coffee and one of Effie‚Äôs homemade cakes! It‚Äôs Mardi Gras now and there are fun events going on at Lumiere so keep an eye on their Facebook page. G&A

name: nabin sapkota
snippet: Lumerie means light! Yes for sure this light won‚Äôt made your taste unlit! Hi this is Nabin!and Its been 7 years cheffing around Oz! Working in a several kitchen ,As a kitchen staff everyone is choosy about workplace!And i choose Lumerie as my work place!Firstly Its my pleasure to work in Lumiere!surprisingly you will get an awosome family environment which is really less in today‚Äôs Sydney! And food is really hygienic,fresh made and delicious! To be honest it‚Äôs mouthwatering! Its not me the one who said this but locals! Come and say hello if you are around us! We won‚Äôt let you down!#cheers -Team Lumerie

name: Lara Low
snippet: Grab a sunny seat outside and bring your dog along for breakfast, brunch or lunch. Service can be slow if most tables are taken so come before mid morning if you are in a rush. The menu has something for most people, making it a local favourite.

name: Lee Gesmundo
snippet: Love this place, food is great and always a great serving size. Coffee is amazing staff always have a smile on their face! Vegan options available!

name: Mighty Brown Mouse
snippet: i forgot to order a 3/4 latte and ended up with a very milky latte which i hate, hence immediately ordered a 3/4 latte. the sweet sweet staff would not charge for the mistake i made. she was so gracious, it made the coffee taste better!

name: Jonathan Ng
snippet: Really friendly staff and great food. The ham and (provolone) cheese croissant was great- basic and no frills but so good.

name: Geoff Cutler
snippet: I had the best ricotta pancakes and berry compote with a caramelised banana. I'm going back to try other items which looked amazing on other people's tables! We had a super friendly staff member attending as well.

name: Nigel
snippet: Quality of the food and service was exceptional, really enjoyed the Lumiere Style Eggs Benedict which was cooked perfectly and the coffee had so much taste, just how I like it

name: Warren Harrington
snippet: Great food and friendly service. The ricotta hotcakes are consistently among the best in Sydney!

name: Albert C
snippet: Great food, very friendly and professional staff, definitely would recommend.Food: 5/5 | Service: 5/5 | Atmosphere: 5/5 ‚Ä¶More

name: Stephen Coombes
snippet: Came in for a coffee. Asked if they did egg n bacon rolls by chance.They said theirs was famous so i gave it a go. Every bite was like spot on.Very happy to return. And get 2 next time.. Milk shake coffee cups should be mandatory. But very satisfied with the quality latte offered

name: D I
snippet: Always a favourite! The team pride themselves on exceptional service and take their menu very seriously. The service is fantastic, and meals freshly prepared. Very popular with locals particularly on weekends, so recommend booking for a table! Meals always make any wait worth it in peak times

name: Aroa Amor
snippet: The food is very nice and portions quiet big. The croissant with prosciutto and poached egg is really good. Also the granola!

name: Helen Lovegrove
snippet: Pleasant helpful staff, good food, stylish cafe in great inner city quadrangle. Highly recommended.

name: J K
snippet: $8.50 for an iced mocha üòÇüòÇüòÇ Please break the cost of that down for us in the comments. :)

name: Anthea Kates
snippet: My favourite cafe in Sydney. Food is always amazing.. the Ricotta Hotcakes are to die for and the coffee even better!!!

name: Ming Zhang
snippet: Wonderful location, friendly staff. The croissant was üëå would recommend to anyone looking for a chill place to spend a morning.

name: Selena Ung
snippet: Great experience! I was actually very excited to go to this place as the name was French (Lumiere means Light). Not all the staff was french though üòÖ Anyway! The staff was amazing and very friendly. The food was really good and the coffee was tasty. They also offered cocktail and I did not resist to have one üôà I would recommend this place! Definitely try their pancakes, soft and sweet. ü•û I don't remember the name of the other dish but the sausage was marvellous ü•ò

name: Anna Wang
snippet: I ordered sour dough with jam - only provided very small amount of butter, not enough to even spread one slice. But more importantly the waitress who served us was really rude, almost seemed like she wanted us to leave asap after eating - she came over 3 times to ask whether a plate with food is done, can she not see there‚Äôs still food there?

name: David Redhill
snippet: Great service by the Brazilian girl with the pink in her hair. Has a very vibrant aura.

name: Garry Bronson
snippet: Came to this cafe for the firs t time yesterday and what an experience. The older gentleman super friendly and very attentive to my needs. I was quite confused by the menu as it is quite big and my waiter Khan helped me out and took me the right path to having the Hotcakes. I must say what a great choice. Highly recommend these boys, very professional and the food is just as good as them. See you soon.

name: Andrew Schultz
snippet: Great food and friendly staff. The corn cakes were delicious and coffee is great. #BeatTheGrind

name: Zae Greenwood
snippet: Absolute must! Perfect example of what a Sydney cafe should be. Wonderful service with style and laughs. Fab food, great coffee and the rose at lunch was üëå will be back! Zx

name: Sofia Gv
snippet: One of the best breakfasts I‚Äôve had in a while. Highly recommend the lumiere eggs Benedict.

name: Ilias Stoikos
snippet: The greatest breakfast/brunch in town. Love your coffee love your Eggs Benedict with Salmon and fresh avocado..... Love the smoothies. Every time I visit the service comes as fresh as the food and always with a smile. This place makes you feel welcome. Congrats to the staff and kitchen.

name: Francis O'Callaghan
snippet: Beautiful food, very attentive service. Staff are friendly and personal. I really enjoyed the whole experience and I look forward to sharing it with other friends.

name: Simon Taylor
snippet: Great service, awesome food and atmosphere. Greek eggs breakfast easily the best brekky I've had in a long time. Hard to choose between all the fantastic options! Great prices too!

name: Irma Rinaudo
snippet: I recently visited Lumiere Cafe, it was the most wonderful cafe experience my little family and I have had thus far. The coffee was outstanding and the lovely chap who served us who‚Äôs name was Kosta was exceptionally attentive and understanding of our needs even with our 4 year old who was quite fussy that day, The food was amazing and I would strongly recommend this place to anyone considering. We will definitely be back soon!! Thank you for a wonderful experience! A very pleased customer.

name: Mark Tyas
snippet: Always great service from the team at Lumiere. Great menu and good prices for brunch when compared to local competition. A standout for maintaining a consistent level of service

name: Zac
snippet: Had the best brunch ever here. The service was impeccable and the food & drinks were outstanding. All of the staff were amazing, including the young lady with the pink hair! Highly recommend

name: Anth

name: Pu Koh
snippet: Had the breakfast burger. Was yummy. But think I got food poisoning from it tho :( Very friendly staff. And service was quick

name: Dianne Howard
snippet: Only been there once last time in Sydney. 4 for breakfast. Food excellent service fantastic coffee to die for. Atmosphere great. Lady who served us was top class and so friendly and obliging. Will definitely go back again next time in Sydney

name: Daniel Goldstein

name: Robert Johnson
snippet: Good service and nice waiter. They deserve generous tips. Sorry l didn't do that today!

name: Will Deasy
snippet: Best place to go in Surry Hills for breakfast. The host here is amazing, she makes the place and best pancakes

name: Kat Kat
snippet: A tasty, light breakfast and a friendly and attentive team. Try the avo smash with peppers for savoury and the crepes for sweet

name: Matthew Ilic

The burek is top shelf and although I nearly always get the meat variety, the cheese and the cheese n spinach are also amazing. Occasionally they do special Burek with bacon, potato, apple, etc....worth a try, always.

name: hyeongsuk Lee
snippet: I ordered a baked egg. But some hair came out of the food. I took it to the kitchen cuz I didn't want to other customers know it. An old woman(waitress) came and said in a bad tone "what do you want? Make new? without saying sorry. I didn't hear "sorry" until I came out after paid all I ordered.

name: Andrew
snippet: Fresh breakfast plate - something different.To the waiter, please write down the orders instead of trying to impress us by remembering everything, because you didn‚Äôt, you made 3 mistakes.

name: George Janev
snippet: This place is awesome. Very true to the name. The Balkans were alive. The open kitchen is buzzing with activity and the coffee is spot on! I got so excited when I first walked past with an empty stomach for breakfast, that all I wanted was Ajvar on toast to feel like I was back home again. Sometimes it's the simplest of things that make you happy, right? üòä I went back the next day and got the Tavche Gravche (beans). I'm home‚ù§

name: Duke Moolenaar
snippet: Jumped off Central station, looked for somewhere to grab a bite and a coffee. Stumbled apon this place and was impressed. Great food, great coffee and great service. Recommended the Ajuar, goats cheese and poached egg on toast. Dietary restrictions: Have GF toast

name: Max Snow
snippet: Really great healthy food and tastes great especially the stuff with the things such as the goat cheese and the mixed grill plate. Not enough places like this in Sydney. Good portion size and value!

name: Eddie Pegoraro
snippet: Amazing coffee, really friendly and attentive staff, and the menu is a unique selection of Balkan dishes. My favourite breakfast is the baked eggs with kolbasi (a Balkan sausage). It also comes with baked eggplant for vegetarians. This place is my new favourite local. Love it.

name: Marko
snippet: Great customer service and superb food! This place is such as welcome addition to the amazing gastronomic line-up in Surry Hills. I've tried several Eastern European and Burek places around Sydney, but I have to say this one is probably the best. The cheese and spinach burek was fresh and well balanced, a tad runny, but very generous with the filling. The kebapi with balkan salads, ajvar and sour dough was fantastic. It had a very distinct taste and you could really tell they were using quality meats. The staff were very friendly and knowledgeable. I'll be back again, next time to try Palachinki crepes with candied orange.

name: Stephen B. Cohen
snippet: Friendly staff, very nicely presented food and generous portions. Highlights of our lunch were the chicken schnitzel and the loaded fries (chips).

name: Yusha
snippet: A very interesting place. The staff is super great, everyone is very nice. The coffee is delicious, and even small mini honey cake was just right for this coffee. Recommend.

name: Shane Krstevski
snippet: Went there for lunch with the family of 5. We ordered the mixed grill, Balkan pleskavica burger, Burek and the Kebapi. The food was amazing and the staff were fantastic. The prices are very reasonable and good value for money. Highly recommend.

name: Satrina Arabani
snippet: The best lunch i‚Äôve had in a long time while living in Sydney for a month and a half now. I selected a few food options from the food warmer (some salads, the homemade flavorful rice, one roast chicken and one grilled). Also, the BEST Decaff Soy Mocha i‚Äôve had, so good as I can‚Äôt have caffeine. Staff and i guess the managers were really lovely and hospitable, will definitely be back!

name: Hatasha Kioa
snippet: Was just looking at the Menu with my friends and the old lad waitress told us in a bad tone to ‚ÄúMove out the way or you won‚Äôt be served‚Äù. There‚Äôs not a lot of space in there, and when you have customers looking at your menu it would be common sense to talk to your customers politely.

name: Abhijeet Chowdhary
snippet: Great Balkan food experience. Moderately priced. Weekends busy. Friendly staff.

name: Nicholas Langley
snippet: This has been one of my favourite local cafes ever since it opened. Interesting Balkan foods you wouldn't get anywhere else, and you can leave filled and refreshed and still get change from a $20. Not to mention the beautiful sun-filled fit out on a corner.

name: Iryna Semenova
snippet: Very authentic place with Balkan food.I love their breakfasts and deserts (especially honey cake)

name: Eba G
snippet: Ordered the Burek with cheese with sausage on the side along with fresh orange juice. The taste of the Burek was pretty bland, however the sausages (can‚Äôt remember what they are called) were really good. If going in with large groups for brunch/ brekkie on the weekend, I‚Äôd recommend yo book in advance. Get‚Äôs really busy around the AM. Staff seemed friendly and really busy.

name: Gwen
snippet: Sooooooooo nice staff!! Friendly and lovely .üòä The Food is delicious.I love this place ! Recommend this restaurant ‚ô•Ô∏è

name: Ari Cinantya
snippet: Staffs are really nice. I came in around 10 am on sat morning and it was not busy. Coffee was ok, and they provide lactose free milk choice as well.

name: John Wilson
snippet: Had an amazing breakfast at this charming cafe. Food was outstanding , service was excellent and quick. Highly recommended

name: Luka Zubcic
snippet: Really happy we found this place. Service and food were both amazing.Food: 5/5 | Service: 5/5 | Atmosphere: 5/5 ‚Ä¶More

name: Alannah E
snippet: Friendly service, warm atmosphere and beautiful/delicious food and drinks.

name: Isabella Jean Andrews
snippet: Every Friday, we look forward to visiting Balkan Butler for their delicious bacon egg coffee brekkie $10 deal. The bacon and egg roll is delicious, especially with added cheese and special sauce! Best quality and value in Sydney! Thank you especially to their lovely , friendly staff. :-)

name: Kim Thompson
snippet: Always friendly, always great coffee. Thanks!

name: Jonathan Toseski
snippet: Amazing authentic delicious Balkan food that takes me back to my childhood. Highly recommend

name: Mike Troller
snippet: Amazing drink, food, service, and value. Well done guys!

name: Hello Robot
snippet: I can‚Äôt say enough good things about The Balkan Butler! It‚Äôs run by a family team, and you can really feel the amazing family atmosphere and friendliness. We are always greeted so well, and treated like family by the owners and all the staff. Very delicious food, at very very reasonable prices. Considering how expensive Surry Hills is, you get really nice portion sizes at a decent price. The staff loads up our plates like we are family! :) Every time I eat there, I feel like I am eating at a family home. I would highly recommend this place to everyone! We have all of our office staff going there at least once a week, because we are constantly recommending them :)

name: Jessica Uzabeaga
snippet: Love this place great traditional and modern mix of macedonian food. Keep up the good work guys üëçüëç

name: Marija Kostadinovikj
snippet: Welcomed by friendly staff members, sparkly clean and well organized area. This people are really passionate about food. Our breakfast was really worth the money. So far one of the best places in Sydney that have delicious Balkan food.

name: Misspiggyexplores
snippet: The coffee was nice! The service was just ok!I haven‚Äôt tried the food yet! üòÉ

name: Vera Ling
snippet: We loved this cafe because it is such a friendly place with special choices of foods inspired by Balkan food. So much of it looks home-made, like the delicious Burek cheese or potato-filled pastry. The portions are generous and not at all expensive. We sat down inside but there are also options to sit outside near the footpath. Food can be served in a very short time in your lunch hour, and you can choose some things from behind hot and cold counters. You'll want to come back and try other specialities.

name: Kelly Tagalan
snippet: They have the best bacon and egg roll I've ever had, hands down. I also love their pastries, all of which are handmade. One item I really enjoy, but have to have sparingly, is their cake de tres leches. This is a beautiful dessert that isn't commonly found in Australia, and the matriarch of this family owned operation makes it with pride. I recommend the coffee on any day, but definitely check out the lunches and the handmade desserts too.

name: Nickie Kezovski
snippet: Great authentic Balkan meals with fresh salad. This place was so wonderful and the service was great. Thank you Nada for your hospitality. We can‚Äôt wait to come back.

name: Lisa Logan
snippet: I love coming here most mornings the barista not only makes the best coffee but he is so welcoming and efficient :) also the avo toast is delish!!

name: Pynylopy
snippet: Beautifully presented fresh food at a very reasonable orice. Friendly attentive staff who are only too happy to explain the dishes. We stumbled across The Balkan Butler whilst in the area for an event, and we're so glad we did. Love the option to sit outside or in an open window. Will definitely return :)

name: Billy
snippet: Great food and service. Would highly recommend the hot food bar!

name: Brendan Dan Tjahjadi
snippet: The burek is a-friggin-mazing!!! Service is brilliant and the atmosphere is very welcoming.

name: Elena Petrova
snippet: The service is outstanding. David, the owner, is a great guy and is very personable. His mum is the queen in the kitchen and such a beautiful lady. She welcomed us with such a warm heart and made sure our order was on point. Amazing Macedonian food from the heart of the Balkans! Must try the Kebapi and the cheese burek. YUM!! They also make delicious coffee!

name: Kate Wheeldon Davies
snippet: A friend and I went in for a quick glass of wine last night, and wow, we wish we didn't have a booking elsewhere for dinner! The staff were so friendly, the atmosphere was beautiful, and the ros√© was perfect. Will definitely be back!

name: Liam Reed
snippet: Absolutely fantastic food and even better service, cannot recommend enough.

name: Mary Pianka
snippet: Scrumptious and rustic home made style Balkan food. Had amazing baked eggs in a rich pepper and tomato sauce. Great coffee and even great service. Friendly too.

name: Nikita Dhulekar

name: Raelene Buvac

name: Shay Green
snippet: Food was amazing and service was even better. Best burek as well! Food was all fresh and amazing, and great sized portions for the price. Loved this cafe, can‚Äôt wait to return!

name: Caleb Charles
snippet: Incredibly friendly staff and great food / coffee. Always very generous with the servings in the takeaway boxes, and all that for a fair price. Fantastic place to grab a bite to eat.

name: Steve Grantham
snippet: Really nice fitout, well appointed cafe. The fellow behind the counter though seemed quite angry and I'm sorry if I upset him with my paltry order of a mere snack for breakfast. You see I'm overweight and don't really eat breakfast. Still, the smile appeared on his face when I paid him. Which was nice. No photo. Used the wifi from the Keg and Butler Pub over the road so kudos to them.

name: aleks rokic
snippet: Modern coffee shop with Balkan twist, everyone is welcoming and warm and burek was melting in my mouth. Going back for more! Lots of space inside as well. Must visit

name: Tiya G

name: Orlando Merlin
snippet: Lovely food, lovely coffee and lovely staff
